fields.eco_name: evidence
fields.definition: "A type of information that is used to support an assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: inference from background scientific knowledge
fields.definition: "A type of curator inference where conclusions are drawn based on the background scientific knowledge of the curator." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: direct assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence resulting from the direct measurement of some aspect of a biological feature." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: reconstitution assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence based on reconstructing a biological sample from its disassociated state to its original state." [ECO:KAV, PMID:26029343]

fields.eco_name: cell fractionation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fractionation evidence where sub-cellular components are separated based on their physical properties such as density in a sucrose density gradient." [ECO:KIM, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: enzymatic activity assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein assay evidence where the catalytic activity of an enzyme is determined." [url:http\://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2213020914000068]

fields.eco_name: experimental evidence
fields.definition: "A type of evidence that is the output of a scientific procedure performed to make a discovery, test a hypothesis, or demonstrate a known fact." [OED:experiment]

fields.eco_name: immunofluorescence evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein detection assay evidence where a fluorescently labeled antibody is used to detect the presence or localization of a biomolecule within a cell." [ECO:MCC, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: expression pattern evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence that is based on characterization of gene expression." [ECO:MCC, GO:IEP]

fields.eco_name: transcript expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of expression pattern evidence where abundance of a transcript is analyzed." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: protein expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of expression pattern evidence resulting from protein abundance quantification techniques." [NBK:22011, PMC:PMC4029002, url:http\://www.informatics.jax.org/glossary/gain-of-function, url:https\://www.thermofisher.com/us/en/home/life-science/protein-biology/protein-biology-learning-center/protein-biology-resource-library/pierce-protein-methods/overview-protein-expression-systems.html]

fields.eco_name: genetic interaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from the effect that a given gene has on another gene or genes, and the products." [ECO:RCT, PMID:11822023]

fields.eco_name: functional complementation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of genetic interaction evidence where a wild-type copy of the gene in question is inserted into a mutant cell to see if it restores the wild-type phenotype in the mutant background." [PMID:27403640]

fields.eco_name: transgenic rescue experiment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of functional complementation evidence resulting from the introduction of a transgene to prevent, or \"rescue\" an organism from a condition." [url:http\://www.mdpi.com/1420-3049/19/9/13932/pdf, url:http\://www.nature.com/gt/journal/v11/n15/full/3302282a.html]

fields.eco_name: mutant phenotype evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence in which an observable phenotypic difference results from a change or mutation in DNA." [GO:IMP]

fields.eco_name: loss-of-function mutant phenotype evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence where a phenotype is associated with altered gene product which lacks the molecular function of the wild-type gene." [SO:0002054]

fields.eco_name: ectopic expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence where a transgenic strain carrying the construct of a promoter cDNA fusion in which a gene of interest is driven by a defined promoter or enhancer is ectopically expressed in the defined pattern to characterize potential cellular properties and functions of a protein of interest." [PMID:10948520, PMID:19301619]

fields.eco_name: anti-sense experiment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence where a phenotype is observed while expressing an anti-sense version of a gene product in a wild-type (for that gene product) background." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: RNAi evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence where an RNA construct is introduced into a cell and the expression of the gene bearing its complementary sequence is suppressed." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: protein inhibition evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence based on the inhibition of the molecular function of a protein." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: physical interaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence that is based on characterization of an interaction between a gene product and another molecule." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: co-purification evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence where a cellular component subunit is isolated as part of purification of its larger complex." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: affinity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence that depends on the strength of the interaction between two entities." [ECO:MCC, MI:0400]

fields.eco_name: protein binding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence resulting from the binding of a molecule to a protein or protein complex." [GO:0005515, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutation]

fields.eco_name: bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein binding evidence where proteins of interest (bait and prey) are covalently linked to incomplete fragments of a third protein (reporter) and expressed in vivo, at which time interaction between bait and prey proteins brings reporter fragments in close enough proximity to allow them to reform and become a functional reporter protein." [ECO:MCC, MI:0090]

fields.eco_name: obsolete nucleic acid hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of experimental genomic evidence resulting from a process in which single stranded nucleic acids are allowed to interact so that complexes, or hybrids, are formed by molecules with sufficiently similar, complementary sequences." [OBI:0302903]

fields.eco_name: structural similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of similarity evidence based on structural similarity of an annotated gene or gene product to another gene or group of genes." [ECO:MCC, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: motif similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of match to sequence model evidence that is based on the presence of a recognized domain or motif in a gene product's (usually protein) primary sequence." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: match to InterPro member signature evidence
fields.definition: "A type of match to sequence model evidence resulting from a positive match of a protein, or set of proteins to a predictive model (signature) in the InterPro database." [PMC:PMC2686546, url:http\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Nucleic+Acid+Hybridization]

fields.eco_name: BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: protein BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of protein BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: nucleotide BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nucleotide BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: author statement supported by traceable reference
fields.definition: "A type of author statement in which the author makes a statement that is not supported by information in that particular publication, but rather can be traced to a reference cited by that publication." [ECO:RCT, GO:TAS]

fields.eco_name: author statement without traceable support
fields.definition: "A type of author statement that is not associated with results presented or a cited reference." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: no evidence data found
fields.definition: "A type of curator inference that results when research finds no evidence information in the scientific literature, at reference databases, or from other resources." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: obsolete not_recorded
transient rescue experiment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of functional complementation evidence resulting from the introduction of nucleic acids, which are not permanently incorporated into the genome, to temporarily prevent, or \"rescue\" an organism from a condition." []

fields.eco_name: obsolete protein assay evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of direct assay evidence resulting from determining the presence, abundance, structure, function, or activity of proteins." [PMID:18429326]

fields.eco_name: immunological assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence resulting from quantitation of the analyte which depends on the reaction of an antigen (analyte) and an antibody." [ERO:0001362, url:http\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK21589/\,http\://cores.ucsf.edu/protein-assay.html]

fields.eco_name: similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of evidence resulting from comparing likeness of distinct biological entities." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: gain-of-function mutant phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from an altered gene product which possesses a new molecular function or a new pattern of gene expression." [SO:0002053, url:http\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3614608/]

fields.eco_name: sequence similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of similarity based on biomolecular sequence." [ECO:MCC, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: spatial pattern of protein expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein expression evidence that accounts for the position of RNA translation to a protein product ranging in scale from differing tissues to regions of an anatomical structure." []

fields.eco_name: spatial pattern of transcript expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcript expression evidence that accounts for the position of transcription ranging in scale from the position of genes on the chromosome to differing tissues to regions of an anatomical structure." []

fields.eco_name: reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of expression pattern evidence that is based on the expression pattern of a reporter gene." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: voucher specimen phenotypic analysis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence based on an authors phenotypic description of a species (or higher-level group), which explicitly references an observation made of a voucher specimen (a specimen with a permanent museum catalog)." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: genetic similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of similarity based on genotype without respect to expression." [ECO:MCC, PhenoScape:IGTS]

fields.eco_name: suppressor/enhancer interaction phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of genetic interaction evidence resulting from a second mutation that either suppresses or enhances the phenotype expressed from an original mutation." [url:http\://biorxiv.org/content/early/2015/10/03/021592, url:http\://www.wormbook.org/chapters/www\:geneticsuppression/geneticsuppression.html]

fields.eco_name: automatically integrated combinatorial evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of automatically integrated combinatorial evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:MCC, ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: double mutant phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from an experiment typically constructed to determine if two different genes have an observable genetic interaction (functional connection) as the result of a mutation occurring in the alleles of the two genes of interest." [ECO:RCT, PMID:18305163]

fields.eco_name: obsolete array experiment evidence
epistatic interaction phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of genetic interaction evidence resulting from the suppression of one allelic effect by an allele at another genetic locus." [PMID:18852697]

fields.eco_name: phenotypic similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of similarity based on the expression of a genotype in an environment." [ECO:MCC, PhenoScape:IPTS]

fields.eco_name: expression microarray evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcript expression evidence resulting from simultaneous profiling of the expression levels of thousands of genes in a single experiment allowing analysis of genes and their networks." [url:http\://www.illumina.com/techniques/microarrays/gene-expression-arrays.html, url:http\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2435252/]

fields.eco_name: experimental phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence that is based on an observable characteristic trait, which is the result of the expression of an organisms genotype in an environment." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: positional similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of stucture locations or arrangements." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: quantitative trait analysis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phenotypic evidence that is based on a gene product that is associated with a quantitative trait locus, but has not been cloned." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence
fields.definition: "A type of expression microarray evidence where expression level is quantified by sample biotin-labeled cRNA (transcribed from an unknown RNA sample) hybridized to DNA oligonuclotides immoblized on a solid surface." [url:https\://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-94-017-9716-0_30]

fields.eco_name: compositional similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of the histological makeup of structures." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: functional complementation in heterologous system evidence
fields.definition: "A type of functional complementation evidence that is based on the insertion of a wild-type copy of a gene into a heterologous organism, with the mutation occurring in a homologous gene." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: yeast one-hybrid evidence
fields.definition: "A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence that is based on a protein-DNA complementation assay where a single promoter acts as bait and is screened against a library of prey transcription factors." [ECO:MCC, MI:0432, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: developmental similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of embryological or post-embryonic orgin of structures." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: yeast 2-hybrid evidence
fields.definition: "A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence that is based on detection of protein-protein interaction by activation of a yeast reporter gene after a bait protein fused to a DNA-binding domain (which has been transfected into a yeast cell) is used to screen a cDNA library of clones fused to an activation domain." [PMID:12734586]

fields.eco_name: differential methylation hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of in vitro methylation assay evidence where methylation-sensitive restriction enzymes are utilized to compare differential methylation between two samples by first shearing DNA, followed by end-blunting, ligation of linkers, methylation sensitive restriction, PCR using linker primers, dye labeling and relative quantification of methylated DNA fragments by two-colored array hybridization to a CpG island microarray for visual assessment." [PMID:18987809]

fields.eco_name: co-immunoprecipitation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunoprecipitation evidence that involves precipitating two or more proteins via binding to an antibody specific to a single protein, followed by protein identification." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: morphological similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of shape, structure, or configuration in structures." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: obsolete Sos-recruitment assay evidence
obsolete experimental genomic evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of experimental evidence that is based on the characterization of an attribute of the genome underlying a gene product." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: split-ubiquitin functional complementation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein fragment functional complementation evidence that is based on detection of protein-protein interaction between a bait and prey protein by in vivo reconstitution of split-ubiquitin (when bait and prey interact) and release of a reporter protein." [PMID:15064465]

fields.eco_name: gene expression similarity evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phenotypic similarity evidence that is based on the categorization of genes by the similarity of expression profiles." [PMID:19958477]

fields.eco_name: far-Western blotting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence that is based on detection of protein-protein interactions by separation of target proteins by SDS-PAGE which are blotted to a membrane, followed by denaturation and renaturation, probing with purified bait proteins, and detection of the target-bait complexes." [PMID:18079728]

fields.eco_name: methylation-specific polymerase chain reaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of in vitro methylation assay evidence resulting from initial modification of DNA by sodium bisulfite, converting all unmethylated cytosines to uracil, and subsequent amplification with primers specific for methylated versus unmethylated DNA." [PMC:PMC38513, PMID:8790415]

fields.eco_name: southern hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of DNA detection assay evidence that is based on detection of a specific DNA sequence by hybridization of labeled probes to any immobilized DNA fragment with sequence similarity." [PMID:18432697]

fields.eco_name: affinity chromatography evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence that results from separation of biochemical mixtures by selective binding of a compound to an immobilized compound on a polymeric matrix, subsequent removal of unattached components, and then displacement of the bound compound." [ECO:MCC, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: phylogenetic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of similarity that indicates common ancestry." [ECO:MCC, PhenoScape:IP]

fields.eco_name: targeting sequence prediction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence that is based on detection of a targeting sequence in the primary sequence of a protein through computational prediction and/or a manual examination of the sequence." [ECO:RCT, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: obsolete polymerase chain reaction evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of experimental genomic evidence where DNA polymerase is used to synthesize new strand of DNA complementary to the offered template strand." [OBI:0000415]

fields.eco_name: transmembrane domain prediction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence that is based on detection of one, or more, transmembrane domains in the primary sequence of a protein through computational prediction and/or a manual examination of the sequence." [ECO:RCT, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: gene neighbors evidence
fields.definition: "A type of genomic context evidence in which a gene product's identity is supported on the basis of the identity of neighboring genes." [ECO:MCC, GOC:MG]

fields.eco_name: immunoprecipitation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein binding evidence where an antibody specific for a target protein is used to precipitate the target protein along with any other molecules (e.g. protein, nucleic acid) that are bound to the target protein." [ECO:MCC, ECO:SW, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: amplification of intermethylated sites evidence
fields.definition: "A type of in vitro methylation assay evidence resulting from a genome-wide estimate of DNA methylation by differential enzymatic digestion of genomic DNA with methylation-sensitive and methylation-insensitive isoschizomers, followed by restrained PCR amplification of sequences methylated at both ends and resolving the PCR products in a denaturing polyacrylamide-sequencing gel to generate fingerprints that consist of multiple anonymous bands that represent the DNA methylome of the cell." [PMID:18987810, url:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/probe/docs/techpcr/]

fields.eco_name: immunolocalization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where antibodies are used to detect the location of molecules or other structures within cells or tissues." [ECO:MCC, ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of curator inference that is based on a combination of experimental evidences or existing models of that system in a related species used for the reconstruction of a biological system." [ECO:MCC, GOC:mg]

fields.eco_name: restriction landmark genomic scanning evidence
fields.definition: "A type of DNA detection assay evidence resulting from the use of restriction enzymes for direct end-labeling of DNA (creating landmarks), followed by high-resolution two-dimensional electrophoresis to visualize the landmarks." [PMID:8388788]

fields.eco_name: immunogold labelling evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunolocalization evidence where the antibodies are labeled with colloidal gold particles whose location is then detected via microscopy." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: epitope-tagged protein immunolocalization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunolocalization evidence in which recombinant proteins fused with epitopes are recognized by antibodies." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: array-based sequence capture evidence
fields.definition: "A type of DNA detection assay evidence evidence where gene sequence or variation is determined or detected by fluorescently-labeled DNA fragments hybridized to sequence-specific oligonucleotides immobilized on an array." [PMID:21049075]

fields.eco_name: obsolete biological assay evidence
cell growth regulation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell growth assay evidence that measures one or more aspects of cell growth over a specified time period to indicate an induced or repressed regulatory effect." [ECO:SW, PomBase:MAH]

fields.eco_name: electrophoretic mobility shift assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence based on an electrophoretic mobility shift of macromolecules, where proteins, nucleic acids, or both, are combined and the resulting mixtures are electrophoresed under native conditions through polyacrylamide or agarose gel to detect interactions/complexes between proteins and/or nucleic acid." [ECO:KIM, ECO:SW, PMID:17703195, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: cDNA to DNA expression microarray evidence
fields.definition: "A type of expression microarray evidence where expression level is quantified by fluroescently-labeled cDNA (reverse transcribed from an unknown RNA sample) hybridized to DNA immobilized on a solid surface." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: obsolete in situ hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of nucleic acid hybridization evidence based on localization of a specific segment of DNA or RNA by the application of a complementary strand of nucleic acid to which a reporter molecule is attached." [url:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/probe/docs/techish/]

fields.eco_name: fractionation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the separation of various cell components while preserving their individual functions." [NBK:26936, url:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK26936/]

fields.eco_name: Affymetrix GeneChip evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence resulting from the use of a proprietary Affymetrix GeneChip System for analyzing complex genetic information." [ERO:0001265]

fields.eco_name: co-fractionation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fractionation evidence resulting from a protein fractionated with other compounds, factors, or macromolecules." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: DNA to cDNA expression microarray evidence
fields.definition: "A type of expression microarray evidence where expression levels are quantified by hybridization of fluorescently-labeled DNA to cDNA (reverse transcribed from an unknown RNA sample) immobilized on a solid surface." [ECO:RCT, PMID:15329382]

fields.eco_name: Nimblegen array evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cDNA to DNA expression microarray evidence resulting from the use of a proprietary NimbleGen array to measure expression levels." [PMID:15607417, url:https\://roche-biochem.jp/pdf/products/microarray/user_guide/SeqCap/SeqCap_UserGuide_Delivery_ver3.0.pdf]

fields.eco_name: northern blot evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcript expression evidence based on electrophoresis and probing to determine levels of RNA expression using a complementary hybridization probe on the separated RNA samples." [ECO:SW, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of RNA detection assay evidence where an RNA transcript is reverse transcribed into cDNA and amplified to qualitatively detect gene expression." [ECO:SW, PMID:11013345, PMID:12901609]

fields.eco_name: RNA protection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nuclease protection assay evidence where mRNA is hybridized with radiolabeled RNA probes after which RNAse is added to digest the unbound, nonresistant single-stranded overhang regions, later the remaining probe target hybrids are purified and resolved on denaturing polyacrylamide gel, and quantified by autoradiography." [ECO:SW, PMID:23457339, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: qualitative western immunoblotting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein expression evidence where proteins are separated using gel electrophoresis, blotted onto a membrane, and probed with an antibody that can be detected via light or radioactive emission." [ECO:SW, PMID:23050259, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: expression library screen evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein expression evidence where a protein of interest is isolated on the basis of its hybridization to an antibody raised to a homologous protein." [ECO:MCC, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: differential hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid hybridization evidence in which preferential or exclusive expression of genes in one cell type or tissue is compared to another cell type or tissue when mRNA from each sample is reverse transcribed, labeled, and hybridized to a cDNA library to compare hybridization patterns." [PMID:14668817]

fields.eco_name: subtractive hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid hybridization evidence in which preferential or exclusive expression of genes in one cell type or tissue are compared to another cell type or tissue when denatured ds-cDNA from the two samples are hybridized, and the common sequences are 'subtracted'." [PMID:11298187]

fields.eco_name: over expression analysis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence in which a gene and/or gene product is investigated in a transgenic organism that has been engineered to overexpress that gene product." [PMID:22419077]

fields.eco_name: protein localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of localization evidence where sub-cellular localization of a protein is determined." [GO:0008104, url:http\://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0019937]

fields.eco_name: fusion protein localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein localization evidence resulting from the fusion of a protein of interest to a labeling protein which has enzymatic activity or fluorescence properties." [MI:0240]

fields.eco_name: green fluorescent protein fusion protein localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the labeling of a protein of interest with green fluorescent protein (GFP) from the jellyfish Aequorea victoria." [PMID:9759496]

fields.eco_name: yellow fluorescent protein fusion protein localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the labeling of a protein of interest with yellow fluorescent protein (YFP), which was created by mutating green fluorescent protein (GFP) of the Aequorea victoria." [MI:0368, url:http\://www.jbc.org/content/276/31/29188.long]

fields.eco_name: beta-glucuronidase fusion protein localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the targeted insertion of the beta-glucuronidase (GUS) coding gene as a reporter gene for the localization of a particular gene product." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: beta-galactosidase fusion protein localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the targeted insertion of the beta-galactosidase coding gene (lacZ) into a specific gene to create a beta-galactosidase-tagged fusion protein." [PMID:23681629]

fields.eco_name: transport assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the activity assessment of transport proteins." [PMID:18401524]

fields.eco_name: nucleic acid binding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence resulting from the binding of a molecule to a nucleic acid." [GO:0003676]

fields.eco_name: ribohomopolymer binding assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence resulting from an enzyme displaying binding activity to specific ribohomopolymer." [PMC:PMC102612]

fields.eco_name: thin layer chromatography evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromatography evidence that uses a thin layer of adsorbent (such as silica gel, alumina, or cellulose) on a flat, inert substrate." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: protein:ion binding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein binding evidence resulting from a metal ion binding to a protein at a specific binding site." [PMID:2377604]

fields.eco_name: Southwestern blot evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence in which DNA-protein binding is detected using labeled DNA as probes, hybridized to electrophoretically separated proteins." [ECO:RCT, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: Northwestern blot evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence in which RNA-protein binding is detected using labeled RNA as probes, hybridized to electrophoretically separated proteins." [ECO:RCT, TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: obsolete in vitro binding evidence
in vitro transcription reconstitution assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reconstitution assay evidence resulting from the use of reconstituted polymerase transcription systems to investigate RNA synthesis." [PMID:9237163]

fields.eco_name: in vitro recombinant protein transcription reconstitution assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of in vitro transcription reconstitution assay evidence resulting from the use of recombinant proteins in preparation of a fully-defined transcription system." [PMID:9237165]

fields.eco_name: heterologous protein expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein expression evidence where a gene from one cell is inserted into a cell that does not typically contain that gene and heterologous protein expression is assessed." [ECO:KAV]

fields.eco_name: protein separation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fractionation evidence resulting from the isolation of a single type of protein from a complex mixture." [ERO:0000526]

fields.eco_name: protein separation followed by direct sequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein separation evidence that is followed by direct protein sequencing whereby a protein's amino acid sequence is determined experimentally by Edman degradation or by mass spectrometry." []

fields.eco_name: protein separation followed by fragment identification evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein separation evidence which then utilizes the screening and identification of small-molecules that bind to proteins." [https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/bi3005126, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5632530/]

fields.eco_name: heterologous system uptake evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transport assay evidence in which the uptake mechanism of a transporter is investigated in a cell that does not normally express that protein." [doi:10.1146/annurev.pp.46.060195.002223, ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: electrophysiology assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where electrical properties of cells or tissues are studied." [ECO:KAV]

fields.eco_name: two-electrode voltage clamp recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of voltage clamp recording evidence which involves using two electrodes inserted into a large cell (often a xenopus oocyte) where one electrode is used to measure the internal potential (voltage) of the cell and the other electrode is used to clamp the current." [ECO:SN, PMID:23529422]

fields.eco_name: transcription assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the detection and quantification of transcribed RNA." [MeSH:D014158, url:https\://bmcmolbiol.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1471-2199-15-7]

fields.eco_name: transcriptional activation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcription assay evidence in which sequence-specific binding proteins that increase transcription of a specific target gene or genes are identified, quantified, and/or analyzed." [url:http\://smcg.ccg.unam.mx/enp-unam/05-TranscripYRegulacion/transcription.pdf]

fields.eco_name: biochemical trait analysis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence in which the biochemical aspect of a mutation is analyzed." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: mutant physiological response evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence in which the physiological response of a mutant when presented with an external stimulus is determined." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: mutant visible phenotype evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence in which traits arising from a mutation are visually examined." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: genomic context evidence
fields.definition: "A type of similarity evidence in which the location of the gene within the genome provides insight into the gene's function or evolutionary insight." [PMID:10958625, PMID:21609955]

fields.eco_name: in vivo assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from a sample of microorganisms or living tissue grown in a medium." [ECO:RCT, url:https\://www.cancer.gov/publications/dictionaries/cancer-terms?cdrid=46352]

fields.eco_name: animal model system study evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence arising from the investigation of an animal model system." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: clinical study evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence arising from a controlled investigation that uses human subjects." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: in vitro assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from a process performed outside the living organism, where the components of an organism have been isolated from their usual biological context, to permit a more detailed or more convenient analysis in an artificial setting." [ECO:RCT, url:https\://www.cancer.gov/publications/dictionaries/cancer-terms?cdrid=45733]

fields.eco_name: obsolete in vitro culture assay evidence
cell-free assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from studies in which cytoplasmic and/or nuclear cellular components from resting, nonstimulated cells, are isolated by ultracentrifugation to provide molecular machinery that can be used in reactions in the absence of many of the other cellular components for the purpose of in vitro protein synthesis, transcription, DNA replication, etc." [PMID:18453125]

fields.eco_name: enzyme inhibition evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein inhibition evidence and enzymatic acitivty evidence where the protein under study is an enzyme." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: sequence alignment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sequence similarity evidence in which an annotation is made based on a manually-reviewed or published sequence alignment" [url:http\://www.geneontology.org/GO.evidence.shtml]

fields.eco_name: sequence orthology evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sequence similarity evidence in which orthology is established by multiple criteria, including amino acid and/or nucleotide sequence comparisons and one or more of the following: phylogenetic analysis, coincident expression, conserved map location, functional complementation, immunological cross-reaction, similarity in subcellular localization, subunit structure, substrate specificity, and response to specific inhibitors." [url:http\://www.geneontology.org/GO.evidence.shtml]

fields.eco_name: match to sequence model evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sequence similarity evidence in which the function of a gene product is predicted based on a sequence-based statistical model." [ECO:MCC] {comment="url:http://www.geneontology.org/GO.evidence.shtml"}

fields.eco_name: automatic assertion
fields.definition: "An assertion method that does not involve human review." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: author statement
fields.definition: "A type of documented statement evidence that is based on an assertion by the author of a paper, which is read by a curator." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: curator inference
fields.definition: "A type of inferential evidence that is based on a conclusion drawn by a curator." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: BLAST evidence
fields.definition: "A type of pairwise sequence alignment evidence obtained with basic local alignment search tool (BLAST)." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: nucleotide BLAST evidence
fields.definition: "A type of BLAST evidence in which nucleotide sequences are aligned." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: protein BLAST evidence
fields.definition: "A type of BLAST evidence in which amino acid or translated nucleotide sequences are aligned." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: BLAST evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of BLAST evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: nucleotide BLAST evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nucleotide BLAST evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: protein BLAST evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of protein BLAST evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial evidence
fields.definition: "A type of evidence in which at least two distinct types of evidence have been integrated." [ECO:MCC, ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of combinatorial analysis that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: biological aspect of descendant evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phylogenetic evidence whereby an aspect of an ancestral gene is inferred through the characterization of an aspect of a descendant gene." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: rapid divergence from ancestral sequence evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phylogenetic evidence characterized by long phylogenetic tree branch lengths following a duplication event." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: phylogenetic determination of loss of key residues evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phylogenetic evidence characterized by the absence of key sequence residues." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: assertion method
fields.definition: "A means by which a statement is made about an entity." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: manual assertion
fields.definition: "An assertion method that involves human review." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: nucleotide sequencing assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sequencing assay that determines the sequence of a biopolymer comprised of nucleotides." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: sequencing assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence where the order of molecules that constitute a biopolymer is determined." [ECO:MCC, OBI:0600047]

fields.eco_name: high throughput nucleotide sequencing assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleotide sequencing assay evidence in which a sequence is derived from a parallelized sequencing technique." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: Illumina sequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of high throughput nucleotide sequencing evidence in which sequence is determined through hybridization of adaptor-ligated DNA to a glass slide on which each fragment is simultaneously clonally amplified, followed by progressive rounds of base incorporation with fluorescently-tagged nucleotides, washing, imaging, and cleavage." [OBI:0000724, PMID:26000844]

fields.eco_name: 454 pyrosequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of high throughput nucleotide sequencing evidence in which the sequence for a ssDNA is determined by addition of primers and then nucleotides, one base pair at a time (which generate a specific fluorescence), to the target strand." [EFO:0005016]

fields.eco_name: SOLiD sequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of high throughput nucleotide sequencing evidence in which sequence is determined through rounds of ligation-based sequencing with fluorescently-labeled Di-base probes and cleavage, after which the template is reset, with a primer offset by one base, for subsequent rounds of ligation." [OBI:0000706]

fields.eco_name: chain termination sequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleotide sequencing assay in which DNA sequence is determined by addition of a primed DNA template to a reaction mixture, followed by addition of DNA polymerase, deoxynucleosidetriphosphates (dNTPs - one of which may be radiolabeled), and one of four di-deoxynucleotidetriphosphates (ddNTPs), after which DNA elongation is terminated and the DNA is separated by size and imaged." [OBI:0000695]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunoprecipitation evidence that is used to identify a protein binding site on a genomic DNA sequence." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation-PCR evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses polymerase chain reaction (PCR) where specific primers are used on the pulled-down DNA for DNA detection." [ECO:MCC, ECO:SW, PMID:18388953]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation-qPCR evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence in which protein-DNA interactions are investigated at known genomic binding sites through a process of ChIP, DNA purification, and finally quantitative polymerase chain reaction (qPCR) for DNA detection." [url:https\://www.diagenode.com/applications/chip-qpcr]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation-seq evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses high-throughput sequencing where immunoprecipitated DNA fragments are funnelled into a massively parallel sequencer to produce multiple short reads for locating binding sites of DNA-associated proteins." [ECO:MCC, ECO:SW, OBI:0000716, PMID:22955991]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation-chip evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses a tiling microarray for the detection of protein-bound DNA regions where chromatin is immunoprecipitated for protein tagging and DNA is sheared from the cross-linked protein-DNA complex to be arrayed revealing the protein-bound genomic regions." [ECO:MCC, ECO:SW, PMID:18388953, PMID:19381927]

fields.eco_name: quantitative polymerase chain reaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of DNA detection assay evidence where the reaction product is quantified in real-time across cycles by means of fluorescent dyes or fluorescent probes for detection and quantification of specific sequences in a DNA sample." [ECO:MCC, ECO:SW]

fields.eco_name: chromosome conformation-based evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence that is based on a five-step technique of cross-linking DNA in vivo, restriction digestion, intramolecular ligation, reversing DNA cross-links, DNA processing, and quantitation that serves to analyze the spatial organization of chromatin in a cell and quantify the number of interactions between genomic loci that are nearby in 3-D space." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: 3C evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by 1) quantifying interactions between a single pair of genomic loci and not multiple interactions and 2) performing polymerase chain reaction (PCR) in the final product quantitation step." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: 4C evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by inverse polymerase chain reaction (inverse PCR) on a prior circularized 3C library followed by product quantitation with a microarray." [ECO:MCC, PMID:17033624]

fields.eco_name: 5C evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by performing ligation-mediated amplification (LMA) prior to product quantitation." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: obsolete chromosome conformation capture-PCR evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of chromosome conformation capture evidence that is derived by performing polymerase chain reaction (PCR) in the quantitation step." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: 3C-qPCR evidence
fields.definition: "A type of 3C evidence evidence that 1) quantifies interactions between a single pair of genomic loci (not multiple interactions) and 2) performs quantitative polymerase chain reaction (qPCR) in the quantitation step." [ECO:MCC, PMID:17641637, PMID:26025624]

fields.eco_name: Hi-C evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by performing immunoprecipitation enrichment of the biotin labelled ligated fragments events prior to sequencing of the library and mapping it to the genome." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: 3C-seq evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by inverse polymerase chain reaction (inverse PCR) on a circularized 3C library prior to product quantitation with multiplexed high-throughput (HT) sequencing." [ECO:MCC, PMID:23411633]

fields.eco_name: anatomical perturbation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from the disruption of a structural feature." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: environmental perturbation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from modification to the surroundings or conditions in which an organism lives or operates." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: tissue ablation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of anatomical perturbation phenotypic evidence resulting from the surgical removal of tissue or subcellular components." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: tissue grafting phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of anatomical perturbation phenotypic evidence resulting from the addition of tissue to an organism through a graft procedure." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of combinatorial analysis that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: automatically integrated combinatorial evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of automatically integrated combinatorial evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: obsolete computational combinatorial evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of computational combinatorial analysis that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: sequence alignment evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of sequence alignment evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: sequence alignment evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of sequence alignment evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: sequence similarity evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of sequence similarity evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: sequence similarity evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of sequence similarity evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: similarity evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of similarity evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: similarity evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of similarity evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: genetic similarity evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of genetic similarity evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: genetic similarity evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of genetic similarity evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: match to sequence model evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of match to sequence model evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: match to sequence model evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of match to sequence model evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: motif similarity evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: motif similarity evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: match to InterPro member signature evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of match to InterPro member signature evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: match to InterPro member signature evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of match to InterPro member signature evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: targeting sequence prediction evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of targeting sequence prediction that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: targeting sequence prediction evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of targeting sequence prediction that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: transmembrane domain prediction evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of transmembrane domain prediction that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: transmembrane domain prediction evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of transmembrane domain prediction that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: sequence orthology evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of sequence orthology evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: sequence orthology evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of sequence orthology evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: enzyme-linked immunoabsorbent assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein detection assay evidence where an antigen is bound to a substrate, and an antibody directly or indirectly linked to an enzyme is utilized to determine the amount of bound antigen which is visualized with a color change in the substrate." [ECO:MCC, ECO:SW, PMID:23949770]

fields.eco_name: flow cytometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence in which cells or particles are characterized by passing them through a light source and monitoring the resultant light scatter or fluorochrome excitation." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: experimental evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: expression pattern evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of expression pattern evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: obsolete array experiment evidence used in manual assertion
Affymetrix GeneChip evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of Affymetrix GeneChip evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: cDNA to DNA expression microarray evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of cDNA to DNA expression microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: differential methylation hybridization evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of differential methylation hybridization evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: expression microarray evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of expression microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: Nimblegen array evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of evidence arising from a Nimblegen array experiment that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: array-based sequence capture evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of array-based sequence capture evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: qualitative western immunoblotting evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of qualitative western immunoblotting evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: expression library screen evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of expression library screen evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: heterologous protein expression evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of heterologous protein expression analysis that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: spatial pattern of protein expression evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of protein expression spatial pattern analysis that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: protein expression evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of protein expression analysis that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: DNA to cDNA expression microarray evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of DNA to cDNA expression microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: differential hybridization evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of differential hybridization experiment that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: RNA protection assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of RNA protection assay that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: spatial pattern of transcript expression evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of spatial pattern of transcript expression analysis that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: subtractive hybridization evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of subtractive hybridization experiment that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: transcript expression evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of transcript expression evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: morpholino experiment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence that uses anti-sense by introducing morpholino oligonucleotides into the cytosol of a cell." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: systematic evolution of ligands by exponential amplification evidence
fields.definition: "A type of evidence arising from a physical interaction analysis where a combinatorial chemistry technique is used to identify oligonucleotides that bind to a target ligand." [ECO:MCC, url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systematic_Evolution_of_Ligands_by_Exponential_Enrichment]

fields.eco_name: bacterial one-hybrid evidence
fields.definition: "A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence that uses bacterial transformation with two plasmids to assess in vivo binding of a DNA-binding domain (bait) and DNA target site (prey)." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: RNA-sequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcript evidence based on high-throughput (HT) sequencing of fragmented cDNA molecules." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: cleavage arrested development evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence where embryonic development proceeds although cytokinesis is blocked." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: cytochalasin experiment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cleavage arrested development that arises after treatment with cytochalasin." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: green fluorescent protein immunolocalization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunolocalization evidence data that was generated using green fluorescent protein (GFP) as a marker." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: beta-galactosidase protein immunolocalization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunolocalization evidence that was generated using LacZ protein as a marker." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: author statement used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of author statement that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: author statement without traceable support used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of author statement without traceable support that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: author statement supported by traceable reference used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of author statement supported by traceable reference that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: curator inference used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of curator inference that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: inference from background scientific knowledge used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of inference from background scientific knowledge that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: no evidence data found used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "An inference that results when research finds no evidence information in the scientific literature, at reference databases, or from other resources that is used in an manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: biological aspect of ancestor evidence
fields.definition: "A type of phylogenetic evidence whereby an aspect of a descendant gene is inferred through the characterization of an aspect of an ancestral gene." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: cap analysis of gene expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcript expression evidence based on high-throughput (HT) sequencing of the 5' ends of cDNA molecules that are selected by a cap-trapper system." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: nano-cap analysis of gene expression evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcript expression evidence based on high-throughput (HT) sequencing of the 5' ends of cDNA molecules that are selected by reverse transcriptase template switching." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: imported information
fields.definition: "A type of documented statement evidence that is based on work performed by a person or group prior to a use by a different person or group." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: imported information used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of imported information that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: imported information used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of imported information that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:MCC]
