fields.eco_name: small molecule detection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of molecule detection assay evidence resulting from the detection and quantification of a small molecule (a low molecular weight (typically < 900 daltons) organic compound), such as lipids, sugars, animo acids, drugs, etc." []

fields.eco_name: localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence in which the sub-cellular location of a protein or nucleic acid sequence is determined." []

fields.eco_name: nucleic acid localization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of localization evidence based on localization of a specific segment of DNA or RNA within tissue by the application of a complementary strand of nucleic acid to which a reporter molecule (i.e. either radio-, fluorescent- or antigen-labeled probe) is attached and quantified using either autoradiography, fluorescence microscopy, or immunohistochemistry." []

fields.eco_name: acetylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where acetylated residues are detected in a protein." [SIB:PG, url:http\://www.perkinelmer.com/resources/technicalresources/applicationsupportknowledgebase/radiometric/acetylation.xhtml]

fields.eco_name: cleavage assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the cleavage of a protein into protein fragments by a protease is detected." [PMID:21121091, PMID:22154596]

fields.eco_name: deacetylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of acetyl groups are detected in a protein." [SIB:PG, url:http\://www.perkinelmer.com/resources/technicalresources/applicationsupportknowledgebase/radiometric/acetylation.xhtml]

fields.eco_name: defarnesylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of farnesyl groups from a protein is detected." [PMID:15556768, PMID:16126733, PMID:16507103, SIB:PG]

fields.eco_name: demethylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of methyl groups from a substrate (RNA/DNA or protein) is detected." [SIB:PG, url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demethylation]

fields.eco_name: desumoylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of sumo groups from a protein is detected." [SIB:PG, url:http\://www.enzolifesciences.com/BML-UW8955/sumoylation-kit/]

fields.eco_name: deubiquitination assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of ubiquitin groups from a protein is detected." [PMID:19692941, SIB:PG]

fields.eco_name: farnesylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where farnesylated residues in proteins are detected." [PMID:9030603, SIB:PG, url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farnesyltransferase]

fields.eco_name: methylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where methylated residues of a substarte (RNA/DNA or protein) are detected." [SIB:PG, url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methylation]

fields.eco_name: palmitoylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where palmitoylated residues in a protein are detected." [PMID:10329400, PMID:17077383, SIB:PG]

fields.eco_name: phosphatase assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of phosphatase groups from a protein is detected." [SIB:PG, url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phosphatase]

fields.eco_name: polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where ADP-ribosylated residues in proteins are detected." [PMID:21870253, PMID:2820766, SIB:PG]

fields.eco_name: protein kinase assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of enzymatic activity assay evidence that measures transfer of a phosphate to a peptide or protein substrate by a protein kinase." [url:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK91991/]

fields.eco_name: sumoylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where sumoylated residues on a protein are detected." [SIB:PG, url:http\://www.enzolifesciences.com/BML-UW8955/sumoylation-kit/]

fields.eco_name: single-cell RNA-sequencing evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of single cell RNA-sequencing evidence that is used in automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: single-cell RNA-sequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of RNA-sequencing evidence that uses a single cell as the source of the RNA." []

fields.eco_name: translation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where de novo protein synthesis is detected." [PMID:18230759, PMID:24901308, SIB:PG]

fields.eco_name: ubiquitination assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where ubiquitinated residues on a protein are detected." [PMID:19692941, SIB:PG]

fields.eco_name: cell growth assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where biological cell development, i.e. an increase in cell mass and size are measured." [GO:0016049, PMID:11057898]

fields.eco_name: cell-based assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the study of cells." []

fields.eco_name: quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence that combines reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction and real time polymerase chain reaction to quantitatively assay for the detection of RNA levels." []

fields.eco_name: quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in automatic assertion.
fields.definition: "A type of quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: colony diameter phenotype evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of colony diameter phenotype evidence that is used in manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: single-cell RNA-sequencing evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of single cell RNA-sequencing evidence that is used in manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: colony diameter phenotype evidence
fields.definition: "A type of colony size phenotypic evidence resulting from measurement of a microbial colony's diameter." []

fields.eco_name: colony diameter phenotype evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of colony diameter phenotype evidence that is used in automatic assertion" []

fields.eco_name: membrane fusion assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence in which a broad variety of physiological processes are measured when two separate membranes merge into a single contiguous membrane." [PMID:1836993]

fields.eco_name: membrane fusion assay evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of membrane fusion assay evidence that is used in automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: membrane fusion assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of membrane fusion assay evidence that is used in manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: spheroplast fusion assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of membrane fusion assay evidence based on the fusion of spheroplasts." []

fields.eco_name: spheroplast fusion assay evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of spheroplast fusion assay evidence used in automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: spheroplast fusion assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of spheroplast fusion assay evidence that is used in manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: liquid chromatography coupled with tandem mass spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mass spectrometry evidence where liquid chromatography is used to separate particles in solution, followed by fragmentation and measurement of the mass-to-charge ratio of the resulting particles to identify the amount and type of material entities present in a sample." []

fields.eco_name: liquid chromatography coupled with tandem mass spectrometry evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of liquid chromatography coupled with tandem mass spectrometry evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: liquid chromatography coupled with tandem mass spectrometry evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of liquid chromatography coupled with tandem mass spectrometry evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: small interfering RNA knockdown evidence
fields.definition: "A type of anti-sense experiment evidence where gene expression is disrupted through the introduction of double-stranded RNA molecules, 20-25 base pairs in length, which operate within the RNA interference pathway." []

fields.eco_name: small interfering RNA knockdown evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of small interfering RNA knockdown evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: small interfering RNA knockdown evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of small interfering RNA knockdown evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: ion trap mass spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mass spectrometry evidence where a combination of magnetic and/or electric fields are utilized to capture charged particles in tandem with mass spectrometry." [PMID:1561330]

fields.eco_name: ion trap mass spectrometry evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of ion trap mass spectrometry evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: ion trap mass spectrometry evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of ion trap mass spectrometry evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: atomic force microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where a mechanical probe is applied to a sample (i.e. a type of scanning probe microscopy) which can result in production of an image (with resolution in the order of fractions of a nanometer), force measurement, or sample manipulation." []

fields.eco_name: atomic force microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of atomic force microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: atomic force microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of atomic force microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: polysome profiling evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence employed to study the associations between multiple ribosomes and mRNA that utilizes density gradient centrifugation to separate out the lysate of cells of interest with the objective of isolating polysomes/polyribosomes which are complexes of an mRNA molecule and two or more ribosomes that act to translate mRNA.  The optical density of the fractions is then determined." [PMID:30545912]

fields.eco_name: polysome profiling evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of polysome profiling evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: polysome profiling evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of polysome profiling evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: multilocus sequence typing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleotide sequencing assay evidence in which DNA sequence variations within a specific set of genes (typically housekeeping genes) are used to characterizes strains by their unique allelic profiles." [PMID:9501229]

fields.eco_name: multilocus sequence typing evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of multilocus sequence typing evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: multilocus sequence typing evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of multilocus sequence typing evidence that is used in a manual assertion" []

fields.eco_name: protein-oligonucleotide microarray binding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein-binding evidence that detects binding of a tagged protein to an array of oligonucleotide probes representing potential binding sites." [PMID:22146299]

fields.eco_name: cell staining evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell-based assay evidence in which living cells are stained with a vital stain, i.e. dye that can be used on living cells without causing cell death." [GOC:MAH]

fields.eco_name: alkaline phosphatase reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of selected genes with the phoA gene to express alkaline phosphatase in periplasmic space for protein tracing." [ECO:SW, PMID:11823238]

fields.eco_name: beta-galactosidase reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of the lacZ gene to a specific promoter for the expression of beta-galactosidase which will appear blue when grown on a X-gal medium." [ECO:SW, PMID:20439410]

fields.eco_name: chloramphenicol acetyltransferase reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of the CAT gene to a specific promoter for the expression of chloramphenicol acetyltransferase which confers resistance to the chloramphenicol antibiotic." [ECO:SW, PMID:1630936]

fields.eco_name: beta-glucuronidase reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence where the beta-glucuronidase enzyme from Escherichia coli is used as the reporter to transform non-fluorescent substrates into fluorescents for detection." [ECO:SW]

fields.eco_name: luciferase reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence where luciferase, an oxidative enzyme, is used as the reporter to detect a gene product with bioluminescence." [ECO:SW, PMID:17623934]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation- exonuclease evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses gama-exonuclease to digest TF-unbound DNA after ChIP for the identification of transcription factor binding site locations with high-resolution data." [ECO:SW, PMID:25249628]

fields.eco_name: electrophoretic mobility shift assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of electrophoretic mobility shift that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SW]

fields.eco_name: reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SW]

fields.eco_name: DNA affinity chromatography evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chromatography evidence where immobilized promoter DNA is labeled and bound to a matrix through which a protein mixture is poured and then eluted to purify specific DNA binding proteins." [ECO:SW, PMID:11694305, PMID:11725488]

fields.eco_name: DNAse footprinting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence where proteins that have been bound to DNA protect a binding site from enzymatic cleavage with DNAse, thereby detecting protein-DNA interactions." [ECO:SW, PMID:212715, PMID:22194258]

fields.eco_name: fluorescence anisotropy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence evidence based on rapid and quantitative analysis of diverse molecular interactions, enzyme activities, and nucleic acid hybridization which uses a fluorophore to measure the binding constants and kinetics of reactions that cause a change in the rotational time of the molecules." [ECO:SW, PMID:20232898]

fields.eco_name: genomic systematic evolution of ligands by exponential amplification evidence
fields.definition: "A type of systematic evolution of ligands by exponential amplification evidence based on a restricted genomic DNA library to identify naturally occurring genomic aptamers and RNA-protein interaction networks with RNA-binding protein as bait and high-throughput sequencing." [ECO:SW, PMID:20541015, PMID:21720957]

fields.eco_name: heteronuclear single quantum coherence spectroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence based on two-dimensional NMR for elucidation of the chemical structure of an isolated or synthesized chemical compound where the characteristic transfer magnetization of a proton to a nitrogen or carbon isotope is monitored by NMR, generating a specific peak in the spectrum." [ECO:SW, PMID:19856946]

fields.eco_name: methidiumpropyl-ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid iron (II) footprinting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence where the synthetic molecule methidiumpropyl-EDTA (MPE) is used to cleave ligand-protected DNA, followed by analysis of the restriction fragments to generate a footprint (i.e. size and location) of small molecule binding sites on the DNA." [ECO:SW, PMID:6225070]

fields.eco_name: copper-phenanthroline footprinting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence where nucleic acid that has been bound to protein is cleaved with 1,10-phenanthroline-copper complex resulting in a high-resolution footprint of sequence-specific protein-DNA contacts." [ECO:SW, PMID:11691942]

fields.eco_name: green fluorescent protein reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of select genes with the green fluorescent protein (GFP) gene for detection with bioluminescence of the gene product when exposed to blue ultraviolet light." [ECO:SW, PMID:11989662]

fields.eco_name: glutathione S-transferase pull-down assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence where a gene is fused with the GST gene and the resulting recombinant bait protein is captured on an immobilized Glutathione affinity ligand and incubated with prey protein to identify and characterize protein-protein interactions." [ECO:SW, PMID:26096507]

fields.eco_name: hydroxyl-radical footprinting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence used to identify protein-binding sites on the DNA molecule where DNA that has been bound to protein is digested with hydroxyl radical produced by reduction of hydrogen peroxide with iron (II), followed by separating the cleavage products on a denaturing electrophoresis gel." [ECO:SW, PMID:18546600, PMID:19378159, PMID:3090544]

fields.eco_name: primer extension assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transcript expression evidence used to determine expression levels of mRNA where a labeled synthetic oligonucleotide primer is annealed to mRNA downstream of the presumed transcription start site of a gene. The mRNA is extended with reverse transcriptase, producing cDNA which is electrophoresed, and the band size is enables determination of the 5' end of the mRNA (i.e. the transcription start site)." [ECO:SW, PMID:23378648]

fields.eco_name: rapid amplification of cDNA ends polymerase chain reaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleotide sequencing assay evidence in which RT-PCR (cDNA synthesis) is first used to produce a cDNA copy of a region of the RNA transcript being investigated followed by PCR to capture either the unknown 5' or 3' end of the transcript for sequencing, depending on whether 5' RACE-PCR or 3' RACE-PCR are being undertaken." [ECO:SW, PMID:17498297, PMID:7685466]

fields.eco_name: survival rate analysis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of knockout evidence based on the survival of an organism in a particular environment where a gene for an enzyme or regulator is knocked out and results are used as a natural reporter." [ECO:SW]

fields.eco_name: x-ray crystallography evidence
fields.definition: "A type of crystallography evidence where a purified sample at high concentration is crystallised and the crystals are exposed to an x ray beam to obtain three dimensional molecular structure of proteins and biological macromolecules." [ECO:SW, PMID:23135450, PMID:24648090]

fields.eco_name: DNA adenine methyltransferase identification evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence used to identify DNA binding sites in eukaryotes where Escherichia coli DNA adenine methyltransferase (Dam) is fused to a transcription factor, co-factor, chromatin-associated protein, or nuclear-associated protein, followed by a methyl-dependent PCR to localize methyltransferase in the region of the binding site." [ECO:SW, PMID:16938559, PMID:17545983, PMID:19588092]

fields.eco_name: isothermal titration calorimetry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence where the absorbed or released heat of a biomolecular binding event is directly measured in a reference cell and sample cell after the addition of a ligand using a microcalorimeter for a complete thermodynamic profile of the molecular interaction." [ECO:SW, PMID:10527727]

fields.eco_name: ultraviolet light footprinting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence where DNA is non-specifically fragmented with ultraviolet light while protein-bound regions are protected from UV damage and strand breakage patterns are analyzed by PAGE and sequenced to detect protein-DNA contacts." [ECO:SW, PMID:2842760, PMID:7602584]

fields.eco_name: methylation interference footprinting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence used to identify protein binding sites on the DNA molecule where multiple copies of a DNA fragment containing a putative TF-binding site are randomly methylated with dimethyl sulfate (DMS) and cleaved at the methyl group, followed by separating the cleavage products on a denaturing electrophoresis gel." [ECO:SW, PMID:1583685]

fields.eco_name: inference of sequence features from visual inspection used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of inference of sequence features from visual inspection that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCJ]

fields.eco_name: ferric uptake regulator titration assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence used to locate and isolate Fur sites where a plasmid library is created and cloned into a cell line with a ferric uptake regulator (Fur)-repressed reporter and the Fur protein is titrated away from its binding site on the reporter, after which the cell is isolated and plasmid extracted for further sequence analysis." [ECO:SW, PMID:10713425, PMID:7642488, PMID:8107138]

fields.eco_name: host colonization assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence in which the colonization or adhesion capacity is measured." []

fields.eco_name: host colonization assay evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of host colonization assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: host colonization assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of host colonization assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: infection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of host colonization assay evidence in which the infection capacity is measured by assessing changes in the host." []

fields.eco_name: infection assay evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of infection assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: infection assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of infection assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: in situ hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of expression pattern evidence in which single-stranded DNA or RNA (probe) are annealed to complementary DNA or RNA in a portion or section of tissue." []

fields.eco_name: in situ hybridization evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of in situ hybridization evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: in situ hybridization evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of in situ hybridization evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: colorimetric in situ hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid localization evidence and in situ hybridization evidence resulting from the use of colorimetric probes to detect complementary sequences of nucleic acids." [PMID:23497040]

fields.eco_name: colorimetric in situ hybridization evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of colorimetric in situ hybridization evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: colorimetric in situ hybridization evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of colorimetric in situ hybridization evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: random mutagenesis of specific target DNA evidence
fields.definition: "A type of random mutagenesis phenotypic evidence resulting from the random mutation of a specifically targeted region of DNA." []

fields.eco_name: random mutagenesis of specific target DNA evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of random mutagenesis of specific target DNA evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: random mutagenesis of specific target DNA evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of random mutagenesis of specific target DNA evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: cell population optical density evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell-based assay evidence in which optical density is used to measure some aspect of a population of cells. Examples of aspects that can affect optical density measurements include, but are not limited to, cell number and cell shape." []

fields.eco_name: cell population optical density evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of cell population optical density evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." []

fields.eco_name: cell population optical density evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of cell population optical density evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: cell viability assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from analyzing the ability of cells to survive or live successfully." [NBK:144065]

fields.eco_name: cell proliferation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from the measurement of the number of cells, which is a reflection of the balance between cell division and cell loss through cell differentiation or cell death." [ECO:RCT] {comment="PMID:11057898", comment="GO:0008283"}

fields.eco_name: DNA synthesis cell proliferation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell proliferation assay evidence resulting from the measure of DNA synthesis in the presece of a label." [PMC:PMC3908118]

fields.eco_name: ATP bioluminescence assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell viability assay evidence resulting from the analysis of ATP concentration (by measuring light intensity) when luciferase catalyzes the oxidation of luciferin in the presence of ATP, magnesium ions and molecular oxygen." [PMID:15344559]

fields.eco_name: cytotoxicity assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of  cell-based assay evidence resulting from the ability of an agent to induce cellular necrosis or apoptosis and the subsequent analysis of cell death mechanism." []

fields.eco_name: obsolete in vitro cell based assay evidence
staining evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the use of stains or dyes to aid in analysis of a microscopic image." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: chemotaxis assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from the evaluation of chemotactic ability (i.e. the movement, or lack of movement, in response to a chemical stimulus) of prokaryotic or eukaryotic cells." [PMC:PMC3667641]

fields.eco_name: genetic transformation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from the conversion of one genotype into another by the introduction of exogenous DNA." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: structure determination evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence resulting from the visualization and examination of chemical and/or molecular structures." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: electron microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence and structure determination evidence resulting from an electron beam utilized to create an image." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: apoptotic assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from the occurrence, visualization, and/or analysis of apoptosis." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: in vivo polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment." [ECO:SN, PMID:2820766, SIB:PG]

fields.eco_name: in vivo polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of in vivo polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: ex vivo assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence derived by studying an organ, tissues, or cells taken from an organism and studied in an external environment with the minimum alteration of natural conditions." [ECO:SN, PMID:16305312, url:http\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2305722/pdf/nihms42807.pdf]

fields.eco_name: two-dimensional polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of gel electrophoresis evidence that involves one dimension electrophoresis where biomolecules are electrophoresed on a low percentage polyacrylamide gel  to be separated in proportion to their mass or isoelectric point, followed by high voltage electrophoresis on a higher percentage gel in the presence of ethidium bromide to alter non-linear molecular shape." [ECO:SW, url:http\://www.nature.com/nmeth/journal/v2/n1/full/nmeth0105-83.html]

fields.eco_name: spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence resulting from the use of a spectrometer." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: regular expression motif search evidence
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence where the motif, a local alignment of sequences, is represented by a regular expression, which captures the variability of nucleotides at each position in a discrete form and can then be used to search genetic sequences by identifying matches to the regular expression." [ECO:SW, PMID:17337630]

fields.eco_name: missense mutation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of point mutation phenotypic evidence resulting from a change in a base (or bases) causing the substitution of one amino acid for another." [SO:0001583]

fields.eco_name: nonsense mutation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of point mutation phenotypic evidence resulting in an incomplete and usually nonfunctional protein product because of a premature stop codon." [url:https\://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/primer/mutationsanddisorders/possiblemutations]

fields.eco_name: silent mutation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of point mutation phenotypic evidence resulting from the change of a DNA nucleotide that does not cause any changes in the amino acid sequence." [url:http\://www.sciencemag.org/news/2006/12/sound-silent-mutation]

fields.eco_name: insertion mutation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from a mutation in which there is an insertion of one or more contiguous nucleotides." [GO:0070705]

fields.eco_name: duplication mutation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from a mutation in which inserted nucleotide(s) have a sequence identical to, or derived from, adjacent nucleotides." [SO:1000035]

fields.eco_name: frameshift mutation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from any mutation that causes an insertion or deletion of nucleotides in a DNA sequence that is not divisible by three and therefore changes the codon reading frame and the translated amino acids." [url:https\://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/primer/mutationsanddisorders/possiblemutations]

fields.eco_name: repeat expansion mutation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from a mutation that increases the number of times that a DNA sequence is repeated." [PMID:9397685, url:https\://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/primer/mutationsanddisorders/possiblemutations]

fields.eco_name: splice site mutation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from a mutation in which there is a change in nucleotides at a splice site." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: translocation mutation phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from a mutation in which a region of a chromosome is transferred to a nonhomologous chromosome." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: molecule detection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence resulting from the detection and analysis of molecular markers." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: protein detection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of molecule detection assay evidence resulting from the detection and quantification of a protein, or multiple proteins." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: RNA detection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of molecule detection assay evidence resulting from the detection of specific RNAs." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: DNA detection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of molecule detection assay evidence resulting from the detection and visualization of a sequence of DNA." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: interferometric reflectance imaging sensor evidence
fields.definition: "A type of molecule detection assay evidence based on changes in surface-reflected light due to ligand binding on the surface of a semi-transparent substrate to detect proteins, DNA, and other biological material in a multiplexed, high-throughput microarray format without labels." [ECO:SW, PMID:21587155, PMID:24271115]

fields.eco_name: S1 nuclease protection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nuclease protection assay evidence where RNA is hybridized with complementary DNA probes and exposed to S1 nuclease for unbound RNA degradation after which the intact RNA is run on a gel for probe size determination and RNA identification to detect and map specific RNAs in a complex mixture of total cellular RNA." [ECO:SW, PMID:21390683]

fields.eco_name: DNA dot blot assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of DNA detection assay evidence resulting from evaluation of the relative abundance of target sequences hybridizing to DNA samples that are immobilized on a nitrocellulose or nylon membrane." [PMID:18265189]

fields.eco_name: DNA dot blot assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of DNA dot blot assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN, ECO:SW]

fields.eco_name: matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization time-of-flight mass spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein detection assay evidence where soft ionization is used for the analysis of biomolecules for mass determination in a three step process of plate preparation, radiation, and ionization with high throughput technology." [ECO:SW, PMID:21964792, PMID:25354905]

fields.eco_name: matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization time-of-flight mass spectrometry evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization time-of-flight mass spectrometry evidence that is  used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN, ECO:SW]

fields.eco_name: site-directed mutagenesis phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype phenotype evidence based on target-specified mutagenesis for the characterization of various gene and protein interactions, structures, and functions where oligonucleotide primers are used to alter a nucleotide sequence." [ECO:SW, PMID:21204030, PMID:24011050, PMID:3541892]

fields.eco_name: random mutagenesis phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence where a mutagenic product or process is used to alter the nucleotide sequence and thus induce genetic mutation.  Examples include, but are not limited to mutagenic compounds, irradiation, PCR w/ degenerate primers, etc." [ECO:SW, PMID:15153637, PMID:18265275]

fields.eco_name: random mutagenesis evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of random mutagenesis phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." []

fields.eco_name: motif discovery evidence
fields.definition: "A type of multiple sequence alignment evidence based on a set of algorithms that infer over-represented motifs from a set of biological sequences returning one or more local multiple sequence alignment defining the inferred motifs." [ECO:SW, PMID:10812473, PMID:16845028, PMID:8211139]

fields.eco_name: consensus search evidence
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence where the motif is represented by a consensus sequence which incorporates the most frequent nucleotide at each position acting as a generic representative for the sequences in the alignment, and is compared to the genetic sequence  for a perfect or imperfect match." [ECO:SW, PMID:15130839]

fields.eco_name: phylogenetic footprinting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of motif discovery evidence based on a set of algorithms that infer motifs in non-coding DNA sequences from the conservation of functional regulatory sites through evolution at a higher rate than their local surroundings for the identification of an evolutionary 'footprint'." [ECO:SW, PMID:16477324, PMID:3199442]

fields.eco_name: comparative genomics motif search evidence
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence based on comparative genomics which uses a search method to scan a set of genomes for instances of a specific motif, and then applies a comparative criterion to analyze the collective strength of these predictions, based on the assumption that functional instances of the motif will be preserved by natural selection and their prediction will therefore be consistent across genomes." [ECO:SW, PMID:10854408]

fields.eco_name: machine learning prediction of motif instance evidence
fields.definition: "A type of match to sequence model evidence which captures the application of a broad suite of supervised and unsupervised machine learning algorithms trained on known motif instances and applied to the prediction of novel putative instances of a motif in a set of biological sequences." [ECO:SW, PMID:17117497, PMID:2014171]

fields.eco_name: position-specific scoring matrix motif search evidence
fields.definition: "A type of motif similarity evidence where the motif is represented by a position-specific frequency matrix (PSFM) that specifies the frequency of each base at each position of the motif, from which a position-specific scoring matrix (PSSM) can be derived under the framework of a log-likelihood ratio providing a scoring system based on the likelihood of a sequence given the motif, versus a genomic-frequency based null hypothesis." [ECO:SW, PMID:10812473]

fields.eco_name: xylE reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of the xylE gene to a specific promoter for the expression of catechol 2,3-dioxygenase that converts the colorless catechol substrate to yellow 2-hydroxymuconic semialdehyde for identification of the expression of a particular gene." [ECO:SW, PMID:2592344]

fields.eco_name: obsolete computationally derived logical inference
obsolete computationally derived logical inference used in automatic assertion
obsolete computationally derived logical inference from automatic assertion used in automatic assertion
obsolete computationally derived logical inference from manual assertion used in automatic assertion
biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from single species used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from single species that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN, PMID:19450514]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from mixed species used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from mixed species that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN, PMID:22232657]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on orthology evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence based on orthology evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on orthology evidence
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence where the evidence is inferred by orthology from an existing experimentally supported model to a process, pathway or complex in another species." [ECO:SN, PMID:15660128]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on paralogy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of  biological system reconstruction evidence based on paralogy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN, PMID:15660128]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on inference from background scientific knowledge used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence based on inference from background scientific knowledge that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN, PMID:17876790]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on inference from background scientific knowledge
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction based solely on background scientific knowledge of that biological system." [ECO:SN, PMID:17876790]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction where the evidence is inferred by homology based on conservation of sequence, function, and composition from an existing experimentally supported model to a process, pathway, or complex." [ECO:SN, PMID:15660128]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on paralogy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of  biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence where the evidence is inferred by paralogy from an existing experimentally supported model to a process, pathway, or complex in the same species." [ECO:SN, PMID:15660128]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence that uses experimental evidence as support." [ECO:SN, PMID:19450514, PMID:22232657]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from mixed species
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence where the experimental evidence is derived by using a mix of species used in the same experiment." [ECO:SN, PMID:22232657]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from single species
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction where the experimental evidence is derived by using multiple experiments in a single species." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: pairwise sequence alignment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sequence alignment evidence where two sequences are aligned to identify regions of similarity that may indicate functional, structural and/or evolutionary relationships between two biological sequences (protein or nucleic acid)." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.ebi.ac.uk/Tools/psa/]

fields.eco_name: multiple sequence alignment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sequence alignment evidence where three or more biological sequences (protein or nucleic acid) of similar length are aligned to infer homology and the evolutionary relationships between the sequences studied." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.ebi.ac.uk/Tools/msa/]

fields.eco_name: multiple sequence alignment evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of multiple sequence alignment evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: multiple sequence alignment evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of multiple sequence alignment evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: motif discovery evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of motif discovery evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: motif discovery evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of motif discovery evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: pairwise sequence alignment evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of pairwise sequence alignment evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: pairwise sequence alignment evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of pairwise sequence alignment evidence that is used in an automatic evidence." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: in-gel protein kinase assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein kinase assay evidence resulting from the evaluation of the phosphorylation activity of kinase on a gel-incorporated kinase substrate." [PMID:12372853]

fields.eco_name: macroscopic current trace evidence
fields.definition: "A type of voltage clamp recording evidence that involves recording trace of the current (pA) going through the analyzed ion channels determined from voltage clamp current recording." [ECO:SN, PMID:17938230, url:http\://www.utdallas.edu/~tres/microelectrode/microelectrodes_ch03.pdf]

fields.eco_name: current density evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electrophysiology assay evidence that involves measuring the amount of current (pA) going through the ion channels per unit  of membrane." [ECO:SN, url:http\://circres.ahajournals.org/content/102/11/1298.full, url:http\://www.bem.fi/book/04/04.htm]

fields.eco_name: obsolete single channel conductance evidence
sustained current evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electrophysiology assay evidence that involves the measurement of the current that persists after the fast and slow inactivation of the analyzed channels." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.nature.com/ncomms/journal/v3/n2/full/ncomms1717.html]

fields.eco_name: obsolete steady state activation curve evidence
obsolete steady state inactivation curve evidence
obsolete window current trace evidence
use dependence of inactivation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electrophysiology assay evidence in which the amount of current remaining after a series of depolarization at different frequencies described as the normalized current related to the time course." [ECO:SN, url:http\://circres.ahajournals.org/content/89/8/700.full]

fields.eco_name: current clamp recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electrophysiology assay evidence that involves recording the change in membrane potential caused by applying specific current to the cell." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.nature.com/nprot/journal/v4/n8/full/nprot.2009.91.html]

fields.eco_name: whole-cell voltage clamp recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of voltage clamp recording evidence that involves direct measurement of ionic current across a membrane while controlling the membrane potential by maintaining the voltage." [ECO:SN, url:http\://circres.ahajournals.org/content/72/1/91.full.pdf]

fields.eco_name: cell-attached single-channel recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of patch-clamp recording evidence that involves isolation of a patch of membrane electrically from the external solution and to record current flowing into the patch and this is achieved by pressing a fire-polished glass pipette, which has been filled with a suitable electrolyte solution, against the surface of a cell and applying light suction." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.utdallas.edu/~tres/microelectrode/microelectrodes_ch04.pdf]

fields.eco_name: cell-detached inside-out single-channel recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of patch-clamp recording evidence that involves study of individual ion channels by gently pulling the patch of membrane away from the cell, and the patch remains attached to the pipette with its cytoplasmic surface exposed to the bathing solution." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.acnp.org/g4/GN401000005/CH005.html]

fields.eco_name: reconstituted bilayer single-channel patch recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of patch-clamp reocrding evidence that involves ion channel analysis by incorporating the ion channels into liposomes suitable for patch-clamping which allows isolation and study of a specific population of channels into that bilayer membrane." [ECO:SN, url:http\://nanion.de/images/stories/papers/Bilayers_lab-on-a-chip08.pdf]

fields.eco_name: voltage clamp recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electrophysiology assay evidence that involves recording membrane potential by controlling the membrane voltage and measuring the transmembrane current required to maintain that voltage." [ECO:SN, url:http\://neurobio.drexelmed.edu/GaoWeb/Resources/Recording%20_Techniques.pdf, url:http\://www.acnp.org/g4/GN401000005/CH005.html]

fields.eco_name: electroencephalography recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electrophysiology assay evidence that involves recording the electrical activity of the brain by means of electrodes placed on the surface of the head." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.jove.com/science-education/5420/electro-encephalography-eeg]

fields.eco_name: super-resolution microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where the images are taken with a higher resolution than the diffraction limit that help in studying nanoscopic sub-cellular structures." [ECO:SN, url:http\://journal.frontiersin.org/article/10.3389/fncel.2015.00007/full]

fields.eco_name: immunogold labelling evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of immunogold labelling evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: flow cytometry evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of flow cytometry evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: enzyme-linked immunoabsorbent assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of enzyme-linked immunoabsorbent assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: cell-detached outside-out single-channel recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of patch-clamp recording evidence where a part of cellular membrane is detached from the cell and whose external face is exposed to the extracellular medium which allows isolating and studying a single or at least a small number of channels into that fragment (patch)." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.nature.com/nprot/journal/v2/n11/full/nprot.2007.403.html]

fields.eco_name: cut-open oocyte voltage clamp recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of voltage clamp recording evidence that involves inserting the oocyte in a chamber that separates the surface into 3 regions where the top portion of the oocyte membrane is the region that is clamped from which currents are actually recorded while the bottom portion is the region of the oocyte that is cut-open, making it possible to inject current intracellularly through a low resistance pathway." [ECO:SN, PMID:9711615]

fields.eco_name: macropatch voltage clamp recording evidence
fields.definition: "A type of voltage clamp recording evidence where recording is done on a fragment of the cell membrane (attached to or detached from the cell) using a large tip diameter pipette that allows isolating and studying a small number of channels into that fragment (patch)." [ECO:SN, url:http\://jxb.oxfordjournals.org/content/50/Special_Issue/1037.full.pdf]

fields.eco_name: high throughput mass spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mass spectrometry evidence where mass-to-charge ratio (m/z) of gas-phase ions is measured which is used to identify and quantify molecules in complex solutions within the framework of high throughput studies." [ECO:SN, PMID:20805795]

fields.eco_name: high throughput mass spectrometry evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of high throughput mass spectrometry evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: confocal microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where sharp images are taken by excluding most of the light from the specimen that is not from the microscope's focal plane, thus allowing better contrast and less haze, which makes it possible to build three-dimensional reconstructions of a volume of the specimen by assembling a series of thin slices taken along the vertical axis." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.physics.emory.edu/faculty/weeks//lab/papers/ebbe05.pdf]

fields.eco_name: wide-field microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where imaging of a thin cell or a tissue specimen is performed by full aperture emission of light gathered by the microscope's objective, which maximizes the recorded signal and simultaneously minimizes the required exposure times." [ECO:SN, url:http\://jcb.rupress.org/content/172/1/9.full, url:http\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3048960/, url:http\://zeiss-campus.magnet.fsu.edu/articles/livecellimaging/techniques.html]

fields.eco_name: confocal microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type confocal microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: wide-field microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of wide-field microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: immunogold labelling electron microscopy assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunogold labelling evidence where electron microscopy technique is used to detect the location of the antibodies labeled with colloidal gold particles." [ECO:SN, PMID:4110101]

fields.eco_name: immunogold labelling electron microscopy assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of immunogold labelling electron microscopy assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: immunodetection assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence that involves the use of antibodies to detect biomolecules." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: immunoperoxidase immunolocalization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunolocalization evidence involving enzymatic detection of a peroxidase tagged antibody." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: immunoperoxidase immunolocalization evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of immunoperoxidase immunolocalization evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: immunoperoxidase immunolocalization electron microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunoperoxidase immunolocalization evidence where electron microscopy technique is used for enzymatic detection of a peroxidase tagged antibody." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: immunoperoxidase immunolocalization electron microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of immunoperoxidase immunolocalization electron microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: wide-field fluorescence microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of wide-field microscopy evidence where pure white and ultraviolet light are produced by a mercury lamp, passed through an optical filter (excitation filter), and directed to a sample via a dichroic mirror, followed by detection of the fluorescent light by a camera after it passes through an emission filter." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.bristol.ac.uk/synaptic/research/techniques/widefield.html]

fields.eco_name: immunofluorescence wide-field microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of wide-field fluorescence microscopy evidence where fluorescently tagged antibodies are imaged that are used to bind to their antigens." [ECO:SN, url:http\://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0057135]

fields.eco_name: immunofluorescence confocal microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of confocal microscopy evidence where light passes through immunofluorescent-stained tissue sections or cells and then the emitted light passes through the dichroic mirror and is focused onto the pinhole for subsequent detection." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.physics.emory.edu/faculty/weeks/confocal/, url:https\://www.hycultbiotech.com/media/wysiwyg/protocol_Immunofluorescence.pdf]

fields.eco_name: immunofluorescence confocal microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of immunofluorescence confocal microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: protein mass spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mass spectrometry evidence where one or more protein analyses are performed." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: cross-streak test evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell proliferation assay evidence where the investigated organism or a potential antagonist is inoculated so as to grow along the diameter line of the agar medium in a Petri dish, then, potentially susceptible microbes (usually bacteria) are streaked perpendicularly to the growth line and inhibition of growth of a test microbe in the vicinity of that line suggests that the antagonist secretes one or more diffusible antibiotics." [ECO:SN, url:www.jstor.org/stable/3792785]

fields.eco_name: disk diffusion test evidence
fields.definition: "A type of zone of inhibition evidence where sensitivity/resistance to an antimicrobial agent is tested by impregnating small filter disks with a known concentration of antimicrobial agent which is then placed on a Mueller-Hinton agar plate inoculated with the test organism." [ECO:SN, url:http\://www.cdc.gov/nczved/resources/cholera/ch9.pdf]

fields.eco_name: cell transfection experiment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence where a foreign genetic material is introduced into the cell for study of gene function and regulation and protein function." [ECO:SN, url:http\://ch.promega.com/resources/product-guides-and-selectors/protocols-and-applications-guide/transfection/, url:http\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2911531/]

fields.eco_name: tethered cell assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chemotaxis assay evidence where the presence or absence of positive or negative chemotaxis is determined by observing the rotational behavior of the cells tethered to a coverslip by their flagella." [ECO:SN, PMID:1103143]

fields.eco_name: tumble frequency assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chemotaxis assay evidence where the presence or absence of positive or negative chemotaxis in swimming organisms is determined by measuring chemotaxis in response to sudden concentration changes from one uniform spatial environment to another." [ECO:SN, PMID:4576832]

fields.eco_name: capillary assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of chemotaxis assay evidence where the presence or absence of positive or negative chemotaxis is determined by measuring the rate of accumulation of the cells into a capillary." [ECO:SN, PMID:4632978]

fields.eco_name: biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: obsolete inference from experimental data evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of direct assay evidence used in manual assertion where phenotype or disease association is made with the gene because of involvement in the molecular mechanism of disease or involvement in a pathway known to contribute to a disease." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: obsolete inference from phenotype manipulation evidence
fields.definition: "OBSOLETE. A type of mutant phenotype evidence used in manual assertion where variations or changes, such as mutations or abnormal levels of the product(s) of a single gene of interest, including non-mutational changes such as inhibition with antibodies or other inhibitors are determined." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: inference by association of genotype from phenotype
fields.definition: "A type of natural variation mutant evidence used in manual assertion where alleles are directly linked to phenotype and Mendelian diseases as a result of various experiments." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: two-dimensional polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of two-dimensional polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: alkaline phosphatase reporter gene assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of alkaline phosphatase reporter gene assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: beta-galactosidase reporter gene assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of beta-galactosidase reporter gene assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: chloramphenicol acetyltransferase reporter gene assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of chloramphenicol acetyltransferase reporter gene assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation-chip evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation-chip evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation- exonuclease evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation- exonuclease evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation-PCR evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation-PCR evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: chromatin immunoprecipitation-seq evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation-seq evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: comparative genomics motif search evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of comparative genomics motif search evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: comparative genomics motif search evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of comparative genomics motif search evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: affinity evidence used in manual assertion

fields.eco_name: protein binding evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence that is used in manual assertion resulting from the binding of a molecule to a protein or protein complex." [GO:0005515]

fields.eco_name: bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence that is used in manual assertion where proteins of interest (bait and prey) are covalently linked to incomplete fragments of a third protein (reporter) and expressed in vivo, at which time interaction between bait and prey proteins brings reporter fragments in close enough proximity to allow them to reform and become a functional reporter protein." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: immunological assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence that is used in manual assertion resulting from quantitation of the analyte which depends on the reaction of an antigen (analyte) and an antibody." [ERO:0001362]

fields.eco_name: yeast one-hybrid evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of hybrid interaction evidence that is used in manual assertion that is based on a protein-DNA complementation assay where a single promoter acts as bait and is screened against a library of prey transcription factors." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: split-ubiquitin functional complementation evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of split-ubiquitin functional complementation evidence that is used in a manual assertion that is based on detection of protein-protein interaction between a bait and prey protein by in vivo reconstitution of split-ubiquitin (when bait and prey interact) and release of a reporter protein." [PMID:15064465]

fields.eco_name: far-Western blotting evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence that is used in a manual assertion that is based on detection of protein-protein interactions by separation of target proteins by SDS-PAGE which are blotted to a membrane, followed by denaturation and renaturation, probing with purified bait proteins, and detection of the target-bait complexes." [PMID:18079728]

fields.eco_name: affinity chromatography evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence that is used in a manual assertion that results from separation of biochemical mixtures by selective binding of a compound to an immobilized compound on a polymeric matrix, subsequent removal of unattached components, and then displacement of the bond compound." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: nucleic acid binding evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence that is used in a manual assertion resulting from the binding of a molecule to a nucleic acid." [GO:0003676]

fields.eco_name: ribohomopolymer binding assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence that is used in a manual assertion resulting from an enzyme displaying binding activity to specific ribohomopolymer." [PMC:PMC102612]

fields.eco_name: protein:ion binding evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of protein binding evidence that is used in a manual assertion resulting from a metal ion binding to a protein at a specific binding site." [PMID:2377604]

fields.eco_name: Southwestern blot evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence that is used in a manual assertion in which DNA-protein binding is detected using labeled DNA as probes, hybridized to electrophoretically separated proteins." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: Northwestern blot evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nucleic acid binding evidence that is used in a manual assertion in which RNA-protein binding is detected using labeled RNA as probes, hybridized to electrophoretically separated proteins." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: systematic evolution of ligands by exponential amplification evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of evidence that is used in a manual assertion arising from a physical interaction analysis where a combinatorial chemistry technique is used to identify oligonucleotides that bind to a target ligand." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: bacterial one-hybrid evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of hybrid interaction evidence that is used in a manual assertion that uses bacterial transformation with two plasmids to assess in vivo binding of a DNA-binding domain (bait) and DNA target site (prey)." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: protein-oligonucleotide microarray binding evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of protein-oligonucleotide microarray binding evidence that is used in a manual assertion that detects binding of a tagged protein to an array of oligonucleotide probes representing potential binding sites." [PMID:22146299]

fields.eco_name: functional complementation evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of genetic interaction evidence that is used in a manual assertion where a wild-type copy of the gene in question is inserted into a mutant cell to see if it restores the wild-type phenotype in the mutant background." [PMID:27403640]

fields.eco_name: transgenic rescue experiment evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of functional complementation evidence that is used in a manual assertion that is used in manual assertion resulting from the introduction of a transgene to prevent, or \"rescue\" an organism from a condition." [url:http\://www.nature.com/gt/journal/v11/n15/full/3302282a.html]

fields.eco_name: transient rescue experiment evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of transient rescue experiment evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: suppressor/enhancer interaction phenotypic evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of suppressor/enhancer interaction phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [url:http\://www.wormbook.org/chapters/www\:geneticsuppression/geneticsuppression.html]

fields.eco_name: double mutant phenotypic evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of double mutant phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: epistatic interaction phenotypic evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of epistatic interaction phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [PMID:18852697]

fields.eco_name: functional complementation in heterologous system evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of functional complementation evidence that is used in a manual assertion that is based on the insertion of a wild-type copy of a gene into a heterologous organism, with the mutation occurring in a homologous gene." [TAIR:TED]

fields.eco_name: temperature-sensitive mutant phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from altered gene function at higher temperatures." [GOC:PG, PMID:19596904]

fields.eco_name: temperature-sensitive mutant phenotypic evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of temperature-sensitive mutant phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [GOC:PG, PMID:19596904]

fields.eco_name: recessive mutant phenotype evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence based on the analysis of a mutation which, in diploid organisms, must be present in both alleles for a phenotype to manifest itself." [GOC:PG, NBK:21578]

fields.eco_name: recessive mutant phenotype evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of mutant phenotype evidence that is used in a manual assertion based on the analysis of a mutation which, in diploid organisms, must be present in both alleles for a phenotype to manifest itself." [GOC:PG, NBK:21578]

fields.eco_name: quantum mechanics/molecular mechanics simulation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of computational evidence where the active site of the molecular system is described with highly accurate quantum theory, while the contribution of the rest of the system is described with molecular mechanical force field." [ECO:SN, PMID:26930454]

fields.eco_name: quantum mechanics/molecular mechanics simulation evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of quantum mechanics/molecular mechanics simulation evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: quantum mechanics/molecular mechanics simulation evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of quantum mechanics/molecular mechanics simulation evidence that is used in manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: molecular mechanics simulation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of computational evidence where the energy of a molecular system is predicted as a function of its conformation." [ECO:SN, url:http\://vergil.chemistry.gatech.edu/courses/chem6485/pdf/molmech.pdf]

fields.eco_name: molecular mechanics simulation evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of molecular mechanics simulation evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: molecular mechanics simulation evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of molecular mechanics simulation evidence that is used in manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: quantum mechanics simulation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of computational evidence where the behavior of matter and light on the atomic and subatomic scale is described." [ECO:SN, url:https\://www.britannica.com/science/quantum-mechanics-physics]

fields.eco_name: quantum mechanics simulation evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of quantum mechanics simulation evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: quantum mechanics simulation evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of quantum mechanics simulation evidence that is used in manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: density functional theory simulation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of quantum mechanics simulation evidence that results from the calculation of ground-state electronic structure of atoms, molecules and solid state materials." [ECO:SN, url:https\://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/physics-and-astronomy/density-functional-theory]

fields.eco_name: density functional theory simulation evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of density functional theory simulation evidence that is used in manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: density functional theory simulation evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of density functional theory simulation evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: documented statement evidence
fields.definition: "A type of evidence in which information is recorded in some documentation system, for example, but not limited to a publication, survey, or medical record." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: medical practitioner statement evidence
fields.definition: "A type of documented statement evidence in which information is stated by a health care professional, for example, but not limited to a doctor, nurse, or psychologist." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: self-reported individual's statement evidence
fields.definition: "A type of documented statement evidence in which information is provided by an individual through means including, but not limited to, paper form, electronic form, or verbal communication, and is captured in a documented record." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: self-reported patient statement evidence
fields.definition: "A type of self-reported individual's statement evidence in which information is provided by a patient in a clinical setting." [ECO:SN]

fields.definition: "A type of documented statement evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]
