fields.eco_name: nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance evidence used for quantification of metabolites or for the determination of chemical structure or composition." [ECO:SN, PMID:16428685, PMID:23036848]

fields.eco_name: nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: nuclear magnetic resonance imaging evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance evidence used to image anatomy and physiological processes." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetic_resonance_imaging]

fields.eco_name: nuclear magnetic resonance imaging evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance imaging evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: nuclear magnetic resonance imaging evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance imaging evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: quantitative western immunoblotting evidence
fields.definition: "A type of qualitative western immunoblotting evidence where detection of the signal is carried out through digital imaging and the signal is normalized with methods such as standard curves built from reference housekeeping proteins or total transferred protein measurements." [ECO:SN, PMID:25852189]

fields.eco_name: quantitative western immunoblotting evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of quantitative western immunoblotting evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: quantitative western immunoblotting evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of quantitatative western immunoblotting evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: mixed support of intron positions by RNA-sequencing alignment evidence
fields.definition: "A type of support of intron positions by RNA-sequencing alignment evidence where RNA-seq alignments from a mixture of samples support all of the intron positions (exon pairs) predicted for a transcript." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: mixed support of intron positions by RNA-sequencing alignment evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of mixed support of intron positions by RNA-sequencing alignment evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: mixed support of intron positions by RNA-sequencing alignment evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of mixed support of intron positions by RNA-sequencing alignment evidence that is used in a manual assertion" [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy-based hydrogen-deuterium exchange evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence resulting from measuring the change in a certain type of NMR spectrum as a result of the spontenaous exchange of hydrogen and deuterium nuclei between the sample and the solvent." [PMID:20960033, PMID:28538145, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrogen%E2%80%93deuterium_exchange#NMR_spectroscopy]

fields.eco_name: proton-based nuclear magnetic resonance evidence
fields.definition: "A type of nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence in which the electromagnetic singal being measured comes from the perturbation of hydrogen nuclei resulting in a one dimensional spectrum." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proton_nuclear_magnetic_resonance]

fields.eco_name: circular dichroism evidence
fields.definition: "A type of spectrometry evidence derived from irradiating a sample with light (either visible, infrared or ultraviolet wavelengths) and observing the difference of absorption of left-handed and right-handed light by the sample by comparing the extent of circular polarization in the incident and the emitted light." [PMID:17464384, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circular_dichroism]

fields.eco_name: synchrotron radiation circular dichroism evidence
fields.definition: "A type of circular dichroism evidence where the source of radiation is radially accelerated particles, most often moving on a circular path in a synchrotron, typically providing lower wavelengths and therefore higher signal-to-noise ratio compared to regular circular dichroism measurements." [PMID:20658968]

fields.eco_name: far-UV circular dichroism evidence
fields.definition: "A type of circular dichroism evidence whose spectrum is in the range of 190-230 nm, providing information mainly about amide bonds and through which the relative proportion of secondary structure elements of a protein can be estimated." [PMID:17464384]

fields.eco_name: near-UV circular dichroism evidence
fields.definition: "A type of circular dichroism evidence whose spectrum is in the range of 250-350 nm , providing information mainly about aromatic residues, i.e. phenylalanine, tyrosine and tryptophan, through which it provides information on the tertiary structure of a protein." [PMID:17464384]

fields.eco_name: cryogenic electron microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electron microscopy evidence where the sample being studied has been cooled to cryogenic temperatures (typically below -153 degrees Celsius) prior to the experiment." [PMID:31078399, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryogenic_electron_microscopy]

fields.eco_name: small-angle X-ray scattering evidence
fields.definition: "A type of light scattering evidence derived from determining the properties of particles in a solution such as size, shape, structure, molecular weight and structural transitions by irradiating the sample with an X-ray beam and the scattered intensity is probed at small angles (typically in the range of 0.1-10 degrees) by a detector." [PMID:26320411, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small-angle_X-ray_scattering]

fields.eco_name: particle scattering evidence
fields.definition: "A type of structure determination evidence derived from determining the properties of particles in a solution such as size, shape, structure, molecular weight, diffusion and interaction strength by irradiating the sample with a particle beam and the scattered intensity is probed at a certain angle by a detector." [DisProt:BalintMeszaros]

fields.eco_name: small-angle neutron scattering evidence
fields.definition: "A type of particle scattering evidence derived from determining the properties of particles in a solution such as size, shape, structure, molecular weight and structural transitions by irradiating the sample with a beam of thermal neutrons and the scattered intensity is probed at small angles (typically in the range of 0.1-10 degrees) by a detector." [PMID:17714935, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small-angle_neutron_scattering]

fields.eco_name: author inference
fields.definition: "A type of inferential evidence where an assertion is derived by the authors of a scientific publication from another assertion and/or primary data via logical inference or other rational means." [DisProt:BalintMeszaros]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial experimental and author inference evidence contained in single publication
fields.definition: "A type of combinatorial experimental and author inference evidence where the experimental results and author inference are contained in a single publication." [ECO:MG]

fields.eco_name: X-ray crystallography-based structural model with missing residue coordinates
fields.definition: "A type of X-ray cystallography evidence in which a structural model is built lacking coordinates for some residues indicating high flexibility or structural disorder in that area of the molecule." [DisProt:BalintMeszaros]

fields.eco_name: X-ray crystallography-based structural model with high relative B-factor values
fields.definition: "A type of X-ray cystallography evidence in which a structural model is built that contains high relative B-factor values indicating flexibility in that area of the molecule." [DisProt:BalintMeszaros]

fields.eco_name: cryogenic electron microscopy-based structural model with missing residue coordinates
fields.definition: "A type of cryogenic electron microscopy evidence in which a structural model is built lacking coordinates for some residues indicating high flexibility or structural disorder in that area of the molecule." [DisProt:BalintMeszaros]

fields.eco_name: cryogenic electron microscopy-based structural model with high relative B-factor values
fields.definition: "A type of cryogenic electron microscopy evidence in which a structural model is built that contains high relative B-factor values indicating flexibility in that area of the molecule." [DisProt:BalintMeszaros]

fields.eco_name: Fourier-transform infrared spectroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of spectrophotometry evidence resulting from the evaluation of a molecule in a fluid or solid state by its ability to alter the transmission of infrared light, where the raw data collected is transformed into the specturm by Fourier transform." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourier-transform_infrared_spectroscopy]

fields.eco_name: heat capacity-based evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence derived from measuring the amount of heat absorbed or released by a sample to monitor chemical reactions, phase transitions or other processes affecting the physical state or chemical composition." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calorimetry]

fields.eco_name: differential scanning calorimetry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of heat capacity-based evidence where the heat required to increase the temperature of the sample is continuously monitored and compared to the heat required to increase the temperature of a reference (having a largely identical composition compared to the sample, such as the empty buffer compared to a protein solution) over a range of temperatures." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_scanning_calorimetry]

fields.eco_name: selective antibody-based structural conformation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunodetection assay evidence that involves the use of antibodies that are selective to conformations of the epitope to which they bind in order to provide information on conformations present in a target molecule." [DisProt:BalintMeszaros]

fields.eco_name: protein hydrogen-deuterium exchange mass spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mass spectrometry evidence derived from measuring changes in mass associated with the isotopic exchange between amide hydrogens of the protein backbone and its surrounding solvent, providing information on the structural state, the dynamics and the intrinsic chemical properties of the underlying amino acid sequence." [PMID:31249422, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrogen%E2%80%93deuterium_exchange#Mass_spectrometry]

fields.eco_name: galactokinase reporter gene assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of the galK gene to a specific promoter for the expression of the enzyme galactokinase." [url:https\://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/007668796608039X]

fields.eco_name: polyadenylated transcript 3'-end-sequencing evidence
fields.definition: "A type of RNA-sequencing evidence based on sequencing of the 3' ends of cDNA molecules that are selected by presence of a polyadenylated tail." [PMID:31617559]

fields.eco_name: colony boundary assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of colony morphology phenotypic evidence based on the presence or absence of a visually apparent boundary formed between colonies of multiple isolates or strains of the same microbial species growing on a solid surface such as that of an agar culture medium." [PMID:18621670]

fields.eco_name: colony boundary assay evidence used in automatic assertion
fields.definition: "A type of colony boundary assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion." [ECO:SN]

fields.eco_name: analytical ultracentrifugation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of molecule detection assay evidence where the hydrodynamic behaviour of macromolecules is used to study their size, shape and interactions, by spinning the sample solution at high centrifugal field (up to above 100000 rpm and 1000000 g), and monitoring the evolution of sample concentration profile versus the axis of rotation." [PMID:12192063]

fields.eco_name: fluorescence polarization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence based on the measurement of the change in the degree of polarization of a fluorophore upon binding to a molecular partner." [PMID:21372817]

fields.eco_name: bait-prey protein pull-down evidence
fields.definition: "A type of bait-prey interaction evidence resulting from an affinity purification in-vitro technique used to detect physical interactions between two or more proteins, where a molecule of interest - a \"bait\" - is immobilized and incubated with a protein source containing putative \"prey\" proteins." [PMID:28667618]

fields.eco_name: rotary shadowing electron microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electron microscopy evidence where a heavy metal is evaporated onto surface adsorbed molecules and macromolecular assemblies allowing high-contrast visualization of both individual macromolecules and the surface structure of macromolecular assemblies." [PMID:19247619]

fields.eco_name: electrospray ionization fourier transform ion cyclotron resonance mass spectrometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of mass spectrometry evidence resulting from the ionization of polar functional groups producing multiple charged ions followed by the detection of ion cyclotron frequencies within a magnetic field, making it suitable for the study of large molecules (>2 kDa)." [PMID:10575730]

fields.eco_name: magnetic resonance evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence in which particles in strong constant magnetic field are perturbed by a weak oscillating magnetic field and the resulting eletromagnetic signal is captured." [ECO:MG]

fields.eco_name: electron paramagnetic resonance evidence
fields.definition: "A type of magnetic resonance evidence in which unpaired electrons in a strong constant magnetic field are perturbed by a weak oscillating magnetic field and the resulting electromagnetic signal is captured." [PMID:21826602, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electron_paramagnetic_resonance]

fields.eco_name: site-directed spin-labelling electron paramagnetic resonance evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electron paramagnetic resonance evidence where the signal is obtained by labeling the protein in specific sites with a functional group (most often a nitroxide) containing an unpaired electron using site-directed mutagenesis." [PMID:21826602, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Site-directed_spin_labeling]

fields.eco_name: deglycosylation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of glycan groups from a substrate (RNA, DNA, or protein) is detected." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glycosylation]

fields.eco_name: protein fragment functional complementation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence that is based on the detection of a protein-protein interaction between a bait and prey protein by reconstitution of a reporter protein serving as a detectable entity (usually an enzyme or a fluorescent protein), the two halves of which are each attached separately to the bait and prey." [PMID:31274323]

fields.eco_name: beta galactosidase functional complementation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein fragment functional complementaion evidence where the interaction between bait and prey assemble a functional beta galactosidase enzyme." [PMID:9237989]

fields.eco_name: GAL4-VP16 functional complementation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein fragment functional complementaion evidence where the interaction between bait and prey assemble a transcriptional activation complex consisting of the GAL4 DNA-binding domain and the transactivation domain from the herpes simplex virus protein VP16." [MI:0728]

fields.eco_name: Raman spectroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of spectrophotometry evidence used to determine a structural fingerprint of the molecule in solution by probing its vibrational modes via the inelastic scattering of photons (called Raman scattering)." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raman_spectroscopy]

fields.eco_name: protein thermal shift assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of temperature-induced protein unfolding evidence that assess thermal denaturation temperature and protein stability under different experimental conditions, e.g. buffer pH or ionic strength, redox potential, usually by means of intrinsic fluorescence or thermofluor." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermal_shift_assay]

fields.eco_name: microscale thermophoresis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence resulting from measuring the change of the fluorescent activity of a molecule as a function of binding to a non-fluorescent partner and its movement in a microspcopic thermal gradient affecting the intensity of fluorescence." [PMID:23270813, url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microscale_thermophoresis]

fields.eco_name: native protein gel electrophoresis evidence
fields.definition: "A type of gel electrophoresis evidence resulting from the use of non-denaturing conditions so that the proteins being measured are in their native structural states." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gel_electrophoresis_of_proteins]

fields.eco_name: turbidity measurement evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the optical properties of a solution is measured in the visible light spectrum, assessing the haziness or cloudiness as a result of the properties of the solutes or the changes in their material states." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turbidity]

fields.eco_name: competitive binding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence derived from an experimental setup where the binding properties of a ligand are assessed by measuring the competition with another ligand with already known binding properties." [PMID:21115850]

fields.eco_name: protein unfolding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of structure determination evidence obtained by monitoring structural changes of a protein as a response to changes of an environmental parameter, such as pH or temperature, or the concentration of a denaturant, such as urea." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equilibrium_unfolding]

fields.eco_name: urea-induced protein unfolding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein unfolding evidence where the unfolding of the protein is triggered by increasing concentrations of urea." [PMID:19708649]

fields.eco_name: pH-induced protein unfolding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein unfolding evidence where the unfolding of the protein is triggered by changes in pH." [PMID:23185611]

fields.eco_name: temperature-induced protein unfolding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein unfolding evidence where the unfolding of the protein is triggered by changes in temperature." [PMID:23185611]

fields.eco_name: cell aggregation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from the analysis of cells irreversibly binding to each other." [PMID:24092433]

fields.eco_name: RNA-protein binding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of affinity evidence resulting from the qualitative and quantitative analysis of the affinity with which a protein binds to RNA." [PMID:30804549]

fields.eco_name: fluorescence microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence that is obtained by using the fluorescence of the studied sample instead of or in addition to the scattering, reflection, attenuation or absorption of light." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluorescence_microscope]

fields.eco_name: viscosity measurement evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence where the viscosity of a solution is measured to quantify the material properties of the solution, or the changes of these properties in response to changing composition or environmental factors." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Viscometer]

fields.eco_name: dynamic fluorescence quenching evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence derived from the decrease (quenching) of fluorescence as a result of the interaction between a fluorescence donor and acceptor in their excited state." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quenching_(fluorescence)]

fields.eco_name: static fluorescence quenching evidence
fields.definition: "A type of physical interaction evidence derived from the decrease (quenching) of fluorescence as a result of the intramolecular interaction between a fluorescence donor and acceptor creating a non-fluorescent ground state." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quenching_(fluorescence)]

fields.eco_name: Congo red staining evidence
fields.definition: "A type of staining evidence where Congo red is used to stain cellular structures including amyloid fibrils and aggregates, cell walls of plants and fungi, and for the outer membrane of Gram-negative bacteria." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congo_red, url:https\://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34431623/]

fields.eco_name: Congo red birefringence evidence
fields.definition: "A type of Congo red staining evidence where the Congo red dye produces an apple-green birefringence when it specifically binds to cross-β-sheets of amyloids which is detectable via cross-polarized light." [url:https\://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34431623/]

fields.eco_name: thioflavin T based fluorescence spectroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence evidence used to assess the formation of amyloid fibrils indicated by an increase in Thioflavin T fluorescence intensity and a characteristic red shift in the emission spectrum upon binding to amyloids." [url:https\://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34431623/]

fields.eco_name: differential scanning fluorimetry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein thermal shift assay evidence where thermal unfolding is monitored by measuring the fluorescence intensity upon interaction with its environment." [url:https\://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19225610/]

fields.eco_name: fluorescence correlation spectroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence evidence that measures fluctuations in fluorescence intensity used to detect biophysical properties of single molecules such as diffusion coefficients and hydrodynamic radii." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluorescence_correlation_spectroscopy, url:https\://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17299036/]

fields.eco_name: intrinsic fluorescence-based protein conformation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence evidence used to study protein conformation by measuring the emissions of aromatic amino acids, specifically tryptophan, tyrosine and, to a minor extent, phenylalanine residues." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluorescence_spectroscopy]

fields.eco_name: stopped-flow fluorescence spectroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence evidence used to study binding kinetics by rapidly mixing two interaction components and then \"stopping\" the reaction in the observation chamber." [url:https\://doi.org/10.1016/bs.mie.2018.09.026]

fields.eco_name: temperature jump relaxation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence evidence where the rates of fast chemical reactions in a solution are measured by the intensity of light absorbed or fluoresced by allowing the reaction mixture to come to an equilibrium, and then perturbing the equilibrium by a rapid temperature rise followed by relaxation of the system to the new equilibrium." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temperature_jump, url:https\://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/0022-3735/16/12/003]

fields.eco_name: structural ensemble generation evidence
fields.definition: "A type of computational structure modeling evidence used to build molecular models of intrinsically disordered proteins to capture the dynamic behaviour of their polypeptide chains. Such tools include EOM, ASTEROIDS and ENSEMBLE." [url:https\://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-20164-1_4]

fields.eco_name: molecular dynamics evidence
fields.definition: "A type of computational evidence used to study the physical movements of atoms and molecules with empirical molecular mechanics force fields." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molecular_dynamics]

fields.eco_name: computational structure modeling evidence
fields.definition: "A type of structure determination evidence in which a computational tool is used to generate a model of structure(s) for a molecule." [ECO:MG]

fields.eco_name: qualitative macroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of macroscopy evidence in which non-numerical observed characteristics or features are captured as text descriptions or categorical assignments." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qualitative_property]

fields.eco_name: quantitative macroscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of macroscopy evidence in which measurement techniques result in numerical data." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantitative_research]

fields.eco_name: sporulation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of direct assay evidence that reflects the presence, absence, and/or amount of spore formation." [url:https\://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/sporulation]

fields.eco_name: asexual sporulation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sporulation assay evidence that reflects the presence, absence, and/or amount of asexual spore formation." [ECO:MG]

fields.eco_name: sexual sporulation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of sporulation assay evidence that reflects the presence, absence, and/or amount of sexual spore formation." [ECO:MG]

fields.eco_name: host-surrogate penetration assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental evidence in which the extent of penetration into a host-surrogate material consisting of a synthetic or other non-living substance is measured." [PHI-base]

fields.eco_name: host penetration assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of host colonization assay evidence in which the extent of penetration into host tissue is measured." [PHI-base]

fields.eco_name: iodine-125-labeled ligand binding evidence
fields.definition: "A type of radioligand binding assay evidence in which iodine-125 label is used to measure receptor-ligand interactions, such as in determining selectivity for a particular ligand." [PMID:22674160]

fields.eco_name: bio-layer interferometry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of molecule detection assay evidence in which the detection of the interaction between molecules is done without the use of labels and is instead based on the phase shift-wavelength correlation created between interference patterns off of two unique surfaces on the tip of a biosensor, where the ligand is immobilized onto a bio compatible biosensor while the analyte is in solution." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bio-layer_interferometry]

fields.eco_name: bait-prey interaction evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein binding evidence in which the use of \"bait\" molecules or proteins allows the purification or identification of a binding partner, the \"prey\"." [ECO:MG]

fields.eco_name: high throughput direct assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of high throughput evidence that is used in a manual assertion derived from the high throughput direct measurement of some aspect of a biological feature." [ECO:MCC]

fields.eco_name: high throughput expression pattern evidence
fields.definition: "A type of high throughput evidence derived from the high throughput characterization of gene expression." [GO:IEP]

fields.eco_name: high throughput expression pattern evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of high throughput evidence that is used in a manual assertion derived from the high throughput characterization of gene expression." [GO:IEP]

fields.eco_name: radioligand binding assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of protein binding evidence in which radioactive ligands are used to measure receptor-ligand interactions, such as in determining selectivity for a particular ligand." [PMID:27471749]

fields.eco_name: radioligand binding assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of radioligand binding assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial experimental and author inference evidence
fields.definition: "A type of combinatorial evidence in which the author draws a conclusion based on a combination of prior scientific background knowledge and evidence from one or more experiments." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial experimental and curator inference evidence
fields.definition: "A type of combinatorial evidence in which the curator draws a conclusion based on a combination of prior scientific background knowledge and evidence from one or more experiments." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial experimental and author inference evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of combinatorial evidence from author knowledge and experimental evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: combinatorial experimental and curator inference evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of combinatorial evidence from curator knowledge and experimental evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: voltammetry evidence
fields.definition: "A type of substance quantification evidence where an electrical gradient potential is applied to analyze an analyte of interest, resulting in a measurement amount of electrical current across the potential range applied." [PMID:28127962]

fields.eco_name: voltammetry evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of voltammetry evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: photoconversion evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence evidence where a molecule tagged with a fluorescent protein is exposed to ultraviolet or blue light to shift the spectral emission properties for visualization." [ECO:RCT, PMID:28574633]

fields.eco_name: photoconversion evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of photoconversion evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: agglutination test evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunological assay evidence that involves observation of visible clumping of antibody and antigen into a complex." [URL:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC380037/]

fields.eco_name: agglutination test evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of agglutination test evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: slide agglutination test evidence
fields.definition: "A type of agglutination test evidence that involves observaiton of visible clumping of antibody and antigen into a complex on a slide." [URL:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC380037/]

fields.eco_name: slide agglutination test evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of slide agglutination test evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: direct Coombs test evidence
fields.definition: "A type of agglutination test evidence that results in detection of nonagglutinating antibodies or complement proteins on red blood cells in vivo." [URL:https\://courses.lumenlearning.com/microbiology/chapter/agglutination-assays/]

fields.eco_name: direct Coombs test evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of direct Coombs test evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: indirect Coombs test evidence
fields.definition: "A type of agglutination test evidence that results in screening of antibodies against red blood cell antigens (other than the A and B antigens) that are unbound in a patient's serum in vitro." [URL:https\://courses.lumenlearning.com/microbiology/chapter/agglutination-assays/]

fields.eco_name: indirect Coombs test evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of indirect Coombs test evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: direct hemagglutination assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of agglutination test evidence where some bacteria and viruses cross-link red blood cells and clump together." [URL:https\://courses.lumenlearning.com/microbiology/chapter/agglutination-assays/]

fields.eco_name: direct hemagglutination assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of direct hemagglutination assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: viral hemagglutination inhibition assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of agglutination test evidence where antiviral antibodies in a patient's serum or in a lab-produced antiserum neutralize the virus and block it from agglutinating the red blood cells." [URL:https\://courses.lumenlearning.com/microbiology/chapter/agglutination-assays/]

fields.eco_name: viral hemagglutination inhibition assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of viral hemagglutination inhibition assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: compement fixation assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunological assay evidence that results in the detection of presence of specific antibodies in the patient's serum based on the use of complement, a biologically labile serum factor." [URL:http\://laboratoryinfo.com/complement-fixation-test/]

fields.eco_name: compement fixation assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of compement fixation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: neutralization test assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of immunogical assay evidence that results in detection of specific neutralizing antibodies in a sample." [PMID:24899440, url:http\://www.creative-biolabs.com/drug-discovery/therapeutics/neutralization-assay.htm?gclid=Cj0KEQjwqvvLBRDIt-D7q7iqiOcBEiQAxi68ERRz00a0x9sWSKSLDu7d5-kMi4AdiLNdUq1mXzePdywaArli8P8HAQ)]

fields.eco_name: neutralization test assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of neutralization test assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: copper transport assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of transport assay evidence where the rate of copper transport is estimated." [URL:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3689948/]

fields.eco_name: copper transport assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of copper transport assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: 5-cyano-2,3-ditolyl tetrazolium chloride staining evidence
fields.definition: "A type of staining evidence that involves the use of the redox dye 5-cyano-2,3-ditolyl tetrazolium chloride to evaluate the respiratory activity of cells." [PMID:1622256]

fields.eco_name: 5-cyano-2,3-ditolyl tetrazolium chloride staining evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of 5-cyano-2,3-ditolyl tetrazolium chloride staining evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: plaque assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell growth assay evidence resulting in direct quantification of infectious virons and antiviral substances through the counting of discrete plaques (infectious units and cellular dead zones) in cell culture." [PMID:25407402]

fields.eco_name: plaque assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of plaque assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: epifluorescence microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence microscopy evidence where the light source is mounted above the specimen and the excitation light passes through the microscope objective lens on its way toward the specimen." [URL:http\://www.rsc.org/publishing/journals/prospect/ontology.asp?id=CMO\:0001096|URL\:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4713126/]

fields.eco_name: epifluorescence microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of epifluorescence microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: transmission electron microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electron microscopy evidence where a beam of electrons are transmitted through an ultra thin specimen forming an image which is magnified and focused onto an imaging device, such as a fluorescent screen, on a layer of photographic film, or to be detected by a sensor such as a CCD camera." [ERO:0000329|URL\:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3907272/]

fields.eco_name: transmission electron microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of transmission electron microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: scanning electron microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of electron microscopy evidence where a focused beam of high-energy electrons is used to generate a variety of signals at the surface of solid specimens." [URL:https\://serc.carleton.edu/research_education/geochemsheets/techniques/SEM.html]

fields.eco_name: scanning electron microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of scanning electron microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: time-lapsed microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where a serial images are taken at regular time points to capture the dynamics of what is being observed." [URL:https\://www.nature.com/subjects/time-lapse-imaging]

fields.eco_name: time-lapsed microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of time-lapsed microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: phase contrast microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where a transparent specimen is illuminated with visible light and small phase shifts in the light passing through the specimen are used to produce an image." [CHMO:0000110]

fields.eco_name: phase contrast microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of phase contrast microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: transmitted light brightfied mircoscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence where a sample is illuminated with transmitted white light from below and observed from above." [BAO:0000457]

fields.eco_name: transmitted light brightfied mircoscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of transmitted light brightfied mircoscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: koehler illumination microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence that results in a bright image without glare and minimum heating of the specimen by employing both field and an aperture iris diaphragm for illumination." [URL:http\://www.gonda.ucla.edu/bri_core/kohler.htm]

fields.eco_name: koehler illumination microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of koehler illumination microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: differential interference contrast microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of microscopy evidence that results in visualization of living cells and transparent specimens by taking advantage of differences in the light refraction of different parts of the specimen." [URL:http\://www.microscopemaster.com/differential-interference-contrast.html]

fields.eco_name: differential interference contrast microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of differential interference contrast microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: extended field laser confocal microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of confocal microscopy evidence that results in creation of a continuous confocal multi-colour mosaic from thousands of individually captured images." [PMID:18627634]

fields.eco_name: extended field laser confocal microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of extended field laser confocal microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: confocal laser scanning microscopy evidence
fields.definition: "A type of confocal microscopy evidence that results in an image that is built up pixel-by-pixel by collecting the emitted photons from the fluorophores in the sample by passing a laser beam through a light source aperture which is then focused by an objective lens into a small area on the surface of the sample." [URL:http\://bitesizebio.com/19958/what-is-confocal-laser-scanning-microscopy/]

fields.eco_name: confocal laser scanning microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of confocal laser scanning microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: light scattering evidence
fields.definition: "A type of structure determination evidence derived from determining the properties of particles in a solution such as size, shape, structure, molecular weight, diffusion and interaction strength by illuminating the sample with a laser beam and the scattered intensity is probed at a certain angle by a detector." [PMID:9013660, url:http\://www.lsinstruments.ch/technology/dynamic_light_scattering_dls/, url:http\://www.soft-matter.uni-tuebingen.de/index.html?dls.html]

fields.eco_name: light scattering evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of light scattering evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: dynamic light scattering assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of light scattering evidence derived by analyzing the fluctuations in the internsity of the scattered light by the particles in motion." [PMID:9013660, url:http\://www.soft-matter.uni-tuebingen.de/index.html?dls.html]

fields.eco_name: dynamic light scattering assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of dynamic light scattering assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: static light scattering assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of light scattering evidence derived by measuring the average intensity of scattered light by the particles at multiple angles." [PMID:9013660]

fields.eco_name: static light scattering assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of static light scattering assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: colony papillation assay phenotypic evidence
fields.definition: "A type of colony morphology phenotypic evidence resulting from the formation of papillae (microcolonies) that protrude outwards from the main colony by mutant cells." [PMID:27447898]

fields.eco_name: colony papillation assay phenotypic evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of colony papillation assay phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: crystal violet staining evidence
fields.definition: "A type of staining evidence that is derived from the use of gentian violet as a general biological stain and an acid-base indicator." [BAO:0002468]

fields.eco_name: crystal violet staining evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of crystal violet staining evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: flow cell biofilm assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of biofilm formation assay evidence derived from in vitro cultivation and evaluation of bacterial biofilms under hydrodynamic conditions of flow." [URL:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3438488/]

fields.eco_name: flow cell biofilm assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of flow cell biofilm assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: bacterial 2-hybrid assay evidence

[URL:http\://www.pnas.org/content/97/13/7382.full.pdf]

fields.eco_name: bacterial 2-hybrid assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of bacterial 2-hybrid assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: phenomic profiling assay evidence
fields.definition: "A type of experimental phenotypic evidence that results from the comparison of phenotype profiles (the physical and biochemical traits of organisms in particular environments) across multiple strains; that is, a meta-analysis of a set of phenotypic patterns from many tests in response to a series of changing genetic and/or environmental factors." [EDAM:topic_3298, PMID:2118507]

fields.eco_name: phenomic profiling assay evidence used in manual assertion
fields.definition: "A type of phenomic profiling assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: colony morphology phenotypic evidence

fields.definition: "A type of colony morphology phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: colony color phenotypic evidence

fields.definition: "A type of colony color phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: colony size phenotypic evidence

fields.definition: "A type of colony size phenotypic evidence that is used in an manual assertion." [ECO:RCT]

fields.eco_name: zone of inhibition evidence
fields.definition: "A type of cell growth assay evidence resulting from assessing the sensitivity or resistance of bacteria or fungi to an antimicrobial agent or chemical by measuring the size of the zone of inhibition that results when the test organism is grown on a solid surface in the presence of the antimicrobial agent or chemical." fields.eco_name: machine learning method evidence
fields.definition: "A type of computational evidence in which computational systems build models based on sample data, known as training data, in order to make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed to do so. Such systems are trained on a combination of existing data about an entity, and are applied to the generation of new labels, such as numerical or textual or categorical." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning]

fields.eco_name: deep learning neural network method evidence
fields.definition: "A type of neural network method evidence which leverages a broad suite of neural network models, which use a combination of data attributes of an entity called features as inputs, and map them to outputs through multiple layers of connected hidden units, whose parameters are learned from data." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_learning, url:https\://storage.googleapis.com/brain-genomics-public/research/proteins/protnlm/uniprot_2022_04/protnlm_preprint_draft.pdf, url:https\://www.uniprot.org/help/ProtNLM]

fields.eco_name: rule-based machine learning method evidence
fields.definition: "A type of machine learning method evidence which uses a combination of data attributes to derive knowledge used to create a set of rules. These rules collectively represent the prediction model and are in the form of \"IF:THEN\" statements. The knowledge applied can be traced back to the rules and the original data." [UniProt:Vishal Joshi, url:https\://borgelt.net/apriori.html, url:https\://www.uniprot.org/help/arba]

fields.eco_name: single molecule fluorescence in situ hybridization evidence
fields.definition: "A type of fluorescence in situ hybridization evidence resulting from the use of fluorescent probes to localize and quantify individual RNA molecules in single cells for studying gene expression." [PMID:29889208]

fields.eco_name: support vector machine evidence
fields.definition: "A type of machine learning method evidence that uses a supervised learning model with associated algorithms for classification. Support vector machines aim to determine a hyperplane that separates two classes while maximizing the distance from the hyperplane to any given data point in those classes." [url:https\://www.nature.com/articles/nbt1206-1565]

fields.eco_name: string-matching method evidence
fields.definition: "A type of computational evidence that employs a string algorithm to identify a string within a larger string or body of text, where a string is a particular series of characters consisting of letters, numbers, symbols, spaces, etc." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/String-searching_algorithm]

fields.eco_name: regular expression method evidence
fields.definition: "A type of string-matching method evidence in which patterns consisting of characters and/or symbols in particular combinations and/or order are used to identify matches in a larger string or body of text." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_expression]

fields.eco_name: neural network method evidence
fields.definition: "A type of machine learning method evidence in which the machine learning model consists of nodes connected to each other with edges that are organized into layers, where the edges can transmit signals between nodes such that the system acts similarly to biological neurons." [url:https\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_neural_network]

fields.eco_name: coordinate mapping to geographic property shapefiles
fields.definition: "A type of computational inference where a geographic property of an entity is determined by searching coordinates associated with the entity against polygons with associated geographic properties in the form of shapefiles." [ENA:Peter]

fields.eco_name: inference of intermediate molecular structure from structure of final molecule
fields.definition: "A type of curator inference in which the structure of a possible intermediate molecule made during a biosynthetic process is inferred based on the structure of the final molecule in the process." [ECO:MG]
